67MachineType MachineTypeFor(maglev::ValueRepresentation repr) {
68 switch (repr) {
69 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
70 return MachineType::AnyTagged();
71 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
72 return MachineType::Int32();
73 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
74 return MachineType::Uint32();
75 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
76 return MachineType::IntPtr();
77 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
78 return MachineType::Float64();
79 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
80 return MachineType::HoleyFloat64();
81 }
82}

86// This reducer tracks the Maglev origin of the Turboshaft blocks that we build
87// during the translation. This is then used when reordering Phi inputs.
88template <class Next>
89class BlockOriginTrackingReducer : public Next {
90 public:
91 TURBOSHAFT_REDUCER_BOILERPLATE(BlockOriginTracking)
92 void SetMaglevInputBlock(const maglev::BasicBlock* block) {
93 maglev_input_block_ = block;
94 }
95 const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_input_block() const {
96 return maglev_input_block_;
97 }
98 void Bind(Block* block) {
99 Next::Bind(block);
100 // The 1st block we bind doesn't exist in Maglev and is meant to hold
101 // Constants (which in Maglev are not in any block), and thus
102 // {maglev_input_block_} should still be nullptr. In all other cases,
103 // {maglev_input_block_} should not be nullptr.
104 DCHECK_EQ(maglev_input_block_ == nullptr,
105 block == &__ output_graph().StartBlock());
106 turboshaft_block_origins_[block->index()] = maglev_input_block_;
107 }
108
109 const maglev::BasicBlock* GetMaglevOrigin(const Block* block) {
110 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(turboshaft_block_origins_[block->index()]);
111 return turboshaft_block_origins_[block->index()];
112 }
113
114 private:
115 const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_input_block_ = nullptr;
116 GrowingBlockSidetable<const maglev::BasicBlock*> turboshaft_block_origins_{
117 __ phase_zone()};
118};

120class GeneratorAnalyzer {
121 // A document explaning how generators are handled by the translation can be
122 // found here:
123 //
124 // https://docs.google.com/document/d/1-iFoVuvpIEjA9dtSsOjmKL5vAzzvf0cKI6f4zaObiV8/edit?usp=sharing
125 //
126 //
127 // Because of generator resumes, Maglev graphs can have edges that bypass loop
128 // headers. This actually happens everytime a loop contains a `yield`.
129 // In Turboshaft, however, the loop header must always dominate every block in
130 // the loop, and thus does not allow such edges that bypass the loop header.
131 // For instance,
132 //
133 // function* foo() {
134 // for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
135 // if (i % 2 == 0) {
136 // yield i;
137 // }
138 // }
139 // }
140 //
141 // The corresponding Maglev graph will look something like (this is a little
142 // bit simplified since details don't matter much for this high level
143 // explanation; the drawing in FindLoopHeaderBypasses below gives a more
144 // precise view of what the Maglev graph looks like):
145 //
146 // + 1 ------+
147 // | Switch |
148 // +---------+
149 // / \
150 // / \ |----------------------|
151 // / \ | |
152 // / v v |
153 // / + 2 --------+ |
154 // / | Loop | |
155 // | +-----------+ |
156 // | | |
157 // | | |
158 // v v |
159 // + 4 ------+ + 3 --------------+ |
160 // | Resume | | Branch(i%2==0) | |
161 // +---------+ +-----------------+ |
162 // | / \ |
163 // | / \ |
164 // | / \ |
165 // | + 5 -------+ | |
166 // | | yield i | | |
167 // | +----------+ | |
168 // | | |
169 // |----------------------------| | |
170 // | | |
171 // v v |
172 // + 6 ----------+ |
173 // | i++ | |
174 // | backedge | |
175 // +-------------+ |
176 // | |
177 // |-------------------|
178 //
179 // In this graph, the edge from block 4 to block 6 bypasses the loop header.
180 //
181 //
182 // Note that it's even possible that the graph contains no forward path from
183 // the loop header to the backedge. This happens for instance when the loop
184 // body always unconditionally yields. In such cases, the backedge is always
185 // reached through the main resume switch. For instance:
186 //
187 // function* foo() {
188 // for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
189 // yield i;
190 // }
191 // }
192 //
193 // Will produce the following graph:
194 //
195 // + 1 ------+
196 // | Switch |
197 // +---------+
198 // / \
199 // / \ |-------------|
200 // / \ | |
201 // / v v |
202 // / + 2 --------+ |
203 // / | Loop | |
204 // | +-----------+ |
205 // | | |
206 // | | |
207 // v v |
208 // + 4 ------+ + 3 -------+ |
209 // | Resume | | yield i | |
210 // +---------+ +----------+ |
211 // | |
212 // | |
213 // |----------------------------------------|
214 //
215 //
216 // GeneratorAnalyzer finds the loop in the Maglev graph, and finds the
217 // generator resume edges that bypass loops headers. The GraphBuilder then
218 // uses this information to re-route such edges to loop headers and insert
219 // secondary switches. For instance, the graph right above will be transformed
220 // to something like this:
221 //
222 // + 1 ------+
223 // | Switch |
224 // +---------+
225 // | |
226 // | |
227 // v v
228 // + 2 --------+
229 // | p1 = phi |
230 // +-----------+
231 // |
232 // | |-----------------------|
233 // | | |
234 // v v |
235 // + 3 -----------------+ |
236 // | Loop | |
237 // | p2 = phi(p1,...) | |
238 // +--------------------+ |
239 // | |
240 // | |
241 // v |
242 // + 4 -----------+ |
243 // | Switch(p2) | |
244 // +--------------+ |
245 // / \ |
246 // / \ |
247 // / \ |
248 // v v |
249 // + 5 --------+ + 6 --------+ |
250 // | Resume | | yield i | |
251 // +-----------+ +-----------+ |
252 // | |
253 // | |
254 // |-------------------------------------|
255
256 public:
257 explicit GeneratorAnalyzer(Zone* phase_zone,
258 maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller* labeller)
259 : labeller_(labeller),
260 block_to_header_(phase_zone),
261 visit_queue_(phase_zone) {
262 USE(labeller_);
263 }
264
265 void Analyze(maglev::Graph* graph) {
266 for (auto it = graph->rbegin(); it != graph->rend(); ++it) {
267 if ((*it)->is_loop()) {
268 FindLoopBody(it);
269 }
270 }
271
272 FindLoopHeaderBypasses(graph);
273 }
274
275 bool JumpBypassesHeader(const maglev::BasicBlock* target) {
276 return block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_.contains(target);
277 }
278
279 const maglev::BasicBlock* GetInnermostBypassedHeader(
280 const maglev::BasicBlock* target) {
281 DCHECK(JumpBypassesHeader(target));
282 return block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_[target];
283 }
284
285 bool HeaderIsBypassed(const maglev::BasicBlock* header) {
286 DCHECK(header->is_loop());
287 return bypassed_headers_.contains(header);
288 }
289
290 const maglev::BasicBlock* GetLoopHeader(const maglev::BasicBlock* node) {
291 if (block_to_header_.contains(node)) {
292 return block_to_header_[node];
293 }
294 return nullptr;
295 }
296
297 bool has_header_bypasses() const { return !bypassed_headers_.empty(); }
298
299 private:
300 // We consider that every block in between the loop header and the backedge
301 // belongs to the loop. This is a little bit more conservative than necessary
302 // and might include blocks that in fact cannot reach the backedge, but it
303 // makes dealing with exception blocks easier (because they have no explicit
304 // predecessors in Maglev).
305 void FindLoopBody(maglev::BlockConstReverseIterator it) {
306 const maglev::BasicBlock* header = *it;
307 DCHECK(header->is_loop());
308
309 --it; // Skipping the header, since we consider its loop header to be the
310 // header of their outer loop (if any).
311
312 const maglev::BasicBlock* backedge_block = header->backedge_predecessor();
313 if (backedge_block == header) {
314 // This is a 1-block loop. Since headers are part of the outer loop, we
315 // have nothing to mark.
316 return;
317 }
318
319 block_to_header_[backedge_block] = header;
320
321 for (; *it != backedge_block; --it) {
322 const maglev::BasicBlock* curr = *it;
323 if (block_to_header_.contains(curr)) {
324 // {curr} is part of an inner loop.
325 continue;
326 }
327 block_to_header_[curr] = header;
328 }
329 }
330
331 void FindLoopHeaderBypasses(maglev::Graph* graph) {
332 // As mentioned earlier, Maglev graphs for resumable generator functions
333 // always start with a main dispatch switch in the 3rd block:
334 //
335 //
336 // + 1 -----------------+
337 // | InitialValues... |
338 // | Jump |
339 // +--------------------+
340 // |
341 // |
342 // v
343 // + 2 --------------------+
344 // | BranchIfRootConstant |
345 // +-----------------------+
346 // / \
347 // / \
348 // / \
349 // / \
350 // v v
351 // + 3 ----------+ + 4 --------------+
352 // | Load state | | Initial setup |
353 // | Switch | | return |
354 // +-------------+ +-----------------+
355 // / | \
356 // / | \
357 // v v v
358 // Resuming in various places
359 //
360 //
361 //
362 // In order to find loop header bypasses, we are looking for cases where
363 // the destination of the dispatch switch (= the successors of block 3) are
364 // inside a loop.
365
366 constexpr int kGeneratorSwitchBLockIndex = 2;
367 maglev::BasicBlock* generator_switch_block =
368 graph->blocks()[kGeneratorSwitchBLockIndex];
369 DCHECK(generator_switch_block->control_node()->Is<maglev::Switch>());
370
371 for (maglev::BasicBlock* target : generator_switch_block->successors()) {
372 const maglev::BasicBlock* innermost_header = GetLoopHeader(target);
373
374 if (innermost_header) {
375 // This case bypasses a loop header.
376 RecordHeadersForBypass(target, innermost_header);
377 }
378 }
379 }
380
381 void RecordHeadersForBypass(maglev::BasicBlock* initial_target,
382 const maglev::BasicBlock* innermost_header) {
383 block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_[initial_target] = innermost_header;
384 bypassed_headers_.insert(innermost_header);
385
386 for (const maglev::BasicBlock* outer_header =
387 GetLoopHeader(innermost_header);
388 outer_header; outer_header = GetLoopHeader(outer_header)) {
389 bypassed_headers_.insert(outer_header);
390 }
391 }
392
393 maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller* labeller_;
394
395 // Map from blocks inside loops to the header of said loops.
396 ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<const maglev::BasicBlock*, const maglev::BasicBlock*>
397 block_to_header_;
398
399 // Map from jump target to the innermost header they bypass.
400 std::unordered_map<const maglev::BasicBlock*, const maglev::BasicBlock*>
401 block_to_innermost_bypassed_header_;
402 // Set of headers that are bypassed because of generator resumes.
403 std::unordered_set<const maglev::BasicBlock*> bypassed_headers_;
404
405 // {visit_queue_} is used in FindLoopBody to store nodes that still need to be
406 // visited. It is an instance variable in order to reuse its memory more
407 // efficiently.
408 ZoneVector<const maglev::BasicBlock*> visit_queue_;
409};

411#define GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(name, deopt_info) \
412 V<FrameState> name; \
413 { \
414 OptionalV<FrameState> _maybe_frame_state = BuildFrameState(deopt_info); \
415 if (!_maybe_frame_state.has_value()) { \
416 DCHECK(bailout_->has_value()); \
417 return maglev::ProcessResult::kAbort; \
418 } \
419 name = _maybe_frame_state.value(); \
420 }

422constexpr bool TooManyArgumentsForCall(size_t arguments_count) {
423 constexpr int kCalleeCount = 1;
424 constexpr int kFrameStateCount = 1;
425 return (arguments_count + kCalleeCount + kFrameStateCount) >
426 std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max();
427}
428
429#define BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(count) \
430 { \
431 if (TooManyArgumentsForCall(count)) { \
432 *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments; \
433 return maglev::ProcessResult::kAbort; \
434 } \
435 }
436
437#define GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state, arguments, \
438 ...) \
439 BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size()); \
440 SetMap(node, GenerateBuiltinCall(node, builtin, frame_state, arguments, \
441 ##__VA_ARGS__));

443// Turboshaft's MachineOptimizationReducer will sometimes detect that the
444// condition for a DeoptimizeIf is always true, and replace it with an
445// unconditional Deoptimize. When this happens, the assembler doesn't emit
446// anything until the next reachable block is bound, which can lead to some
447// Variable or OpIndex being Invalid, which can break some assumptions. To avoid
448// this, the RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE macro can be used to early-return.
449#define RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE() \
450 if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) { \
451 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue; \
452 }

454// TODO(dmercadier): LazyDeoptOnThrow is currently not very cleanly dealt with.
455// In Maglev, it is a property of the ExceptionHandlerInfo, which is use by all
456// throwing nodes and is created in a single place
457// (MaglevGraphBuilder::AttachExceptionHandlerInfo). However, during the
458// translation, we create different kind of calls from different places (Call,
459// CallBuiltin_XXX, CallRuntime_XXX), and non-call nodes can also
460// LazyDeoptOnThrow (such as GenericBinop) and we always have to manually
461// remember to pass ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow, which is easy to forget, which can
462// then easily lead to bugs. A few ideas come to mind:
463//
464// - Make ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow non-optional on all throwing nodes. This is a
465// bit verbose, but at least we won't forget it.
466//
467// - Make ThrowingScope automatically annotate all throwing nodes that are
468// emitted while the scope is active. The Assembler would be doing most of
469// the work: it would have a "LazyDeoptOnThrowScope" or something similar,
470// and any throwing node emitted during this scope would have the
471// LazyDeoptOnThrow property added as needed. All throwing nodes have a
472// {lazy_deopt_on_throw} field defined by THROWING_OP_BOILERPLATE (except
473// calls, but we could add it), so it shouldn't be very hard for the
474// Assembler to deal with this in a unified way.
475// The downside of this approach is that the interaction between this and
476// {current_catch_block} (in particular with nested scopes) might introduce
477// even more complexity and magic in the assembler.
478
479class GraphBuildingNodeProcessor {
480 public:
481 using AssemblerT =
482 TSAssembler<BlockOriginTrackingReducer, MaglevEarlyLoweringReducer,
483 MachineOptimizationReducer, VariableReducer,
484 RequiredOptimizationReducer, ValueNumberingReducer>;
485
486 GraphBuildingNodeProcessor(
487 PipelineData* data, Graph& graph, Zone* temp_zone,
488 maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* maglev_compilation_unit,
489 std::optional<BailoutReason>* bailout)
490 : data_(data),
491 temp_zone_(temp_zone),
492 assembler_(data, graph, graph, temp_zone),
493 maglev_compilation_unit_(maglev_compilation_unit),
494 node_mapping_(temp_zone),
495 block_mapping_(temp_zone),
496 regs_to_vars_(temp_zone),
497 loop_single_edge_predecessors_(temp_zone),
498 maglev_representations_(temp_zone),
499 generator_analyzer_(temp_zone,
500 maglev_compilation_unit_->graph_labeller()),
501 bailout_(bailout) {}
502
503 void PreProcessGraph(maglev::Graph* graph) {
504 for (maglev::BasicBlock* block : *graph) {
505 block_mapping_[block] =
506 block->is_loop() ? __ NewLoopHeader() : __ NewBlock();
507 }
508 // Constants are not in a block in Maglev but are in Turboshaft. We bind a
509 // block now, so that Constants can then be emitted.
510 __ Bind(__ NewBlock());
511
512 if (maglev_compilation_unit_->bytecode()
513 .incoming_new_target_or_generator_register()
514 .is_valid()) {
515 // The Maglev graph might contain a RegisterInput for
516 // kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister later in the graph, which in
517 // Turboshaft is represented as a Parameter. We create this Parameter
518 // here, because the Instruction Selector tends to be unhappy when
519 // Parameters are defined late in the graph.
520 int new_target_index = Linkage::GetJSCallNewTargetParamIndex(
521 maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count());
522 new_target_param_ = __ Parameter(
523 new_target_index, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), "%new.target");
524 }
525
526 if (graph->has_resumable_generator()) {
527 generator_analyzer_.Analyze(graph);
528
529 dummy_object_input_ = __ SmiZeroConstant();
530 dummy_word32_input_ = __ Word32Constant(0);
531 dummy_float64_input_ = __ Float64Constant(0);
532
533 header_switch_input_ = __ NewVariable(RegisterRepresentation::Word32());
534 loop_default_generator_value_ = __ Word32Constant(kDefaultSwitchVarValue);
535 generator_context_ =
536 __ NewLoopInvariantVariable(RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
537 __ SetVariable(generator_context_, __ NoContextConstant());
538 }
539
540 // Maglev nodes often don't have the NativeContext as input, but instead
541 // rely on the MaglevAssembler to provide it during code generation, unlike
542 // Turboshaft nodes, which need the NativeContext as an explicit input if
543 // they use it. We thus emit a single NativeContext constant here, which we
544 // reuse later to construct Turboshaft nodes.
545 native_context_ =
546 __ HeapConstant(broker_->target_native_context().object());
547 }
548
549 void PostProcessGraph(maglev::Graph* graph) {
550 // It can happen that some Maglev loops don't actually loop (the backedge
551 // isn't actually reachable). We can't know this when emitting the header in
552 // Turboshaft, which means that we still emit the header, but then we never
553 // come around to calling FixLoopPhis on it. So, once we've generated the
554 // whole Turboshaft graph, we go over all loop headers, and if some turn out
555 // to not be headers, we turn them into regular merge blocks (and patch
556 // their PendingLoopPhis).
557 for (Block& block : __ output_graph().blocks()) {
558 if (block.IsLoop() && block.PredecessorCount() == 1) {
559 __ output_graph().TurnLoopIntoMerge(&block);
560 }
561 }
562 }
563
564 // The Maglev graph for resumable generator functions always has the main
565 // dispatch Switch in its 3rd block.
566 bool IsMaglevMainGeneratorSwitchBlock(
567 const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_block) {
568 if (!generator_analyzer_.has_header_bypasses()) return false;
569 constexpr int kMainSwitchBlockId = 3;
570 bool is_main_switch_block =
571 maglev_compilation_unit_->graph_labeller()->BlockId(maglev_block) ==
572 kMainSwitchBlockId;
573 DCHECK_IMPLIES(is_main_switch_block,
574 maglev_block->control_node()->Is<maglev::Switch>());
575 return is_main_switch_block;
576 }
577
578 maglev::BlockProcessResult PreProcessBasicBlock(
579 maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_block) {
580 // Note that it's important to call SetMaglevInputBlock before calling Bind,
581 // so that BlockOriginTrackingReducer::Bind records the correct predecessor
582 // for the current block.
583 __ SetMaglevInputBlock(maglev_block);
584
585 is_visiting_generator_main_switch_ =
586 IsMaglevMainGeneratorSwitchBlock(maglev_block);
587
588 Block* turboshaft_block = Map(maglev_block);
589
590 if (__ current_block() != nullptr) {
591 // The first block for Constants doesn't end with a Jump, so we add one
592 // now.
593 __ Goto(turboshaft_block);
594 }
595
596#ifdef DEBUG
597 loop_phis_first_input_.clear();
598 loop_phis_first_input_index_ = -1;
599 catch_block_begin_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
600#endif
601
602 if (maglev_block->is_loop() &&
603 (loop_single_edge_predecessors_.contains(maglev_block) ||
604 pre_loop_generator_blocks_.contains(maglev_block))) {
605 EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock(maglev_block);
606 }
607
608 if (maglev_block->is_exception_handler_block()) {
609 StartExceptionBlock(maglev_block);
610 return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
611 }
612
613 // SetMaglevInputBlock should have been called before calling Bind, and the
614 // current `maglev_input_block` should thus already be `maglev_block`.
615 DCHECK_EQ(__ maglev_input_block(), maglev_block);
616 if (!__ Bind(turboshaft_block)) {
617 // The current block is not reachable.
618 return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
619 }
620
621 if (maglev_block->is_loop()) {
622 // The "permutation" stuff that comes afterwards in this function doesn't
623 // apply to loops, since loops always have 2 predecessors in Turboshaft,
624 // and in both Turboshaft and Maglev, the backedge is always the last
625 // predecessors, so we never need to reorder phi inputs.
626 return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
627 } else if (maglev_block->is_exception_handler_block()) {
628 // We need to emit the CatchBlockBegin at the begining of this block. Note
629 // that if this block has multiple predecessors (because multiple throwing
630 // operations are caught by the same catch handler), then edge splitting
631 // will have already created CatchBlockBegin operations in the
632 // predecessors, and calling `__ CatchBlockBegin` now will actually only
633 // emit a Phi of the CatchBlockBegin of the predecessors (which is exactly
634 // what we want). See the comment above CatchBlockBegin in
635 // TurboshaftAssemblerOpInterface.
636 catch_block_begin_ = __ CatchBlockBegin();
637 }
638
639 // Because of edge splitting in Maglev (which happens on Bind rather than on
640 // Goto), predecessors in the Maglev graph are not always ordered by their
641 // position in the graph (ie, block 4 could be the second predecessor and
642 // block 5 the first one). However, since we're processing the graph "in
643 // order" (because that's how the maglev GraphProcessor works), predecessors
644 // in the Turboshaft graph will be ordered by their position in the graph.
645 // Additionally, optimizations during the translation (like constant folding
646 // by MachineOptimizationReducer) could change control flow and remove
647 // predecessors (by changing a Branch into a Goto for instance).
648 // We thus compute in {predecessor_permutation_} a map from Maglev
649 // predecessor index to Turboshaft predecessor index, and we'll use this
650 // later when emitting Phis to reorder their inputs.
651 predecessor_permutation_.clear();
652 if (maglev_block->has_phi() &&
653 // We ignore this for exception phis since they have no inputs in Maglev
654 // anyways, and in Turboshaft we rely on {regs_to_vars_} to populate
655 // their inputs (and also, Maglev exception blocks have no
656 // predecessors).
657 !maglev_block->is_exception_handler_block()) {
658 ComputePredecessorPermutations(maglev_block, turboshaft_block, false,
659 false);
660 }
661 return maglev::BlockProcessResult::kContinue;
662 }
663
664 void ComputePredecessorPermutations(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_block,
665 Block* turboshaft_block,
666 bool skip_backedge,
667 bool ignore_last_predecessor) {
668 // This function is only called for loops that need a "single block
669 // predecessor" (from EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock). The backedge should
670 // always be skipped in thus cases. Additionally, this means that when
671 // even when {maglev_block} is a loop, {turboshaft_block} shouldn't and
672 // should instead be the new single forward predecessor of the loop.
673 DCHECK_EQ(skip_backedge, maglev_block->is_loop());
674 DCHECK(!turboshaft_block->IsLoop());
675
676 DCHECK(maglev_block->has_phi());
677 DCHECK(turboshaft_block->IsBound());
678 DCHECK_EQ(__ current_block(), turboshaft_block);
679
680 // Collecting the Maglev predecessors.
681 base::SmallVector<const maglev::BasicBlock*, 16> maglev_predecessors;
682 maglev_predecessors.resize_no_init(maglev_block->predecessor_count());
683 for (int i = 0; i < maglev_block->predecessor_count() - skip_backedge;
684 ++i) {
685 maglev_predecessors[i] = maglev_block->predecessor_at(i);
686 }
687
688 predecessor_permutation_.clear();
689 predecessor_permutation_.resize_and_init(maglev_block->predecessor_count(),
690 Block::kInvalidPredecessorIndex);
691 int index = turboshaft_block->PredecessorCount() - 1;
692 // Iterating predecessors from the end (because it's simpler and more
693 // efficient in Turboshaft).
694 for (const Block* pred : turboshaft_block->PredecessorsIterable()) {
695 if (ignore_last_predecessor &&
696 index == turboshaft_block->PredecessorCount() - 1) {
697 // When generator resumes bypass loop headers, we add an additional
698 // predecessor to the header's predecessor (called {pred_for_generator}
699 // in EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock). This block doesn't have Maglev
700 // origin, we thus have to skip it here. To compensate,
701 // MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs will take an additional input for these
702 // cases.
703 index--;
704 continue;
705 }
706 // Finding out to which Maglev predecessor {pred} corresponds.
707 const maglev::BasicBlock* orig = __ GetMaglevOrigin(pred);
708 auto orig_index = *base::index_of(maglev_predecessors, orig);
709
710 predecessor_permutation_[orig_index] = index;
711 index--;
712 }
713 DCHECK_EQ(index, -1);
714 }
715
716 // Exceptions Phis are a bit special in Maglev: they have no predecessors, and
717 // get populated on Throw based on values in the FrameState, which can be raw
718 // Int32/Float64. However, they are always Tagged, which means that retagging
719 // happens when they are populated. This can lead to exception Phis having a
720 // mix of tagged and untagged predecessors (the latter would be automatically
721 // retagged). When this happens, we need to manually retag all of the
722 // predecessors of the exception Phis. To do so:
723 //
724 // - If {block} has a single predecessor, it means that it won't have
725 // exception "phis" per se, but just values that have to retag.
726 //
727 // - If {block} has multiple predecessors, then we need to do the retagging
728 // in the predecessors. It's a bit annoying because we've already bound
729 // and finalized all of the predecessors by now. So, we create new
730 // predecessor blocks in which we insert the taggings, patch the old
731 // predecessors to point to the new ones, and update the predecessors of
732 // {block}.
733 void StartExceptionBlock(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler) {
734 Block* turboshaft_catch_handler = Map(maglev_catch_handler);
735 if (turboshaft_catch_handler->PredecessorCount() == 0) {
736 // Some Assembler optimizations made this catch handler not be actually
737 // reachable.
738 return;
739 }
740 if (turboshaft_catch_handler->PredecessorCount() == 1) {
741 StartSinglePredecessorExceptionBlock(maglev_catch_handler,
742 turboshaft_catch_handler);
743 } else {
744 StartMultiPredecessorExceptionBlock(maglev_catch_handler,
745 turboshaft_catch_handler);
746 }
747 }
748 void StartSinglePredecessorExceptionBlock(
749 maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler,
750 Block* turboshaft_catch_handler) {
751 if (!__ Bind(turboshaft_catch_handler)) return;
752 catch_block_begin_ = __ CatchBlockBegin();
753 if (!maglev_catch_handler->has_phi()) return;
754 InsertTaggingForPhis(maglev_catch_handler);
755 }
756 // InsertTaggingForPhis makes sure that all of the inputs of the exception
757 // phis of {maglev_catch_handler} are tagged. If some aren't tagged, it
758 // inserts a tagging node in the current block and updates the corresponding
759 // Variable.
760 void InsertTaggingForPhis(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler) {
761 DCHECK(maglev_catch_handler->has_phi());
762
763 IterCatchHandlerPhis(maglev_catch_handler, [&](interpreter::Register owner,
764 Variable var) {
765 DCHECK_NE(owner, interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
766 V<Any> ts_idx = __ GetVariable(var);
767 DCHECK(maglev_representations_.contains(ts_idx));
768 switch (maglev_representations_[ts_idx]) {
769 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
770 // Already tagged, nothing to do.
771 break;
772 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
773 __ SetVariable(var, __ ConvertInt32ToNumber(V<Word32>::Cast(ts_idx)));
774 break;
775 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
776 __ SetVariable(var,
777 __ ConvertUint32ToNumber(V<Word32>::Cast(ts_idx)));
778 break;
779 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
780 __ SetVariable(
781 var,
782 Float64ToTagged(
783 V<Float64>::Cast(ts_idx),
784 maglev::Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi));
785 break;
786 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
787 __ SetVariable(
788 var, HoleyFloat64ToTagged(V<Float64>::Cast(ts_idx),
789 maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged::
790 ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi));
791 break;
792 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
793 UNREACHABLE();
794 }
795 });
796 }
797 void StartMultiPredecessorExceptionBlock(
798 maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler,
799 Block* turboshaft_catch_handler) {
800 if (!maglev_catch_handler->has_phi()) {
801 // The very simple case: the catch handler didn't have any Phis, we don't
802 // have to do anything complex.
803 if (!__ Bind(turboshaft_catch_handler)) return;
804 catch_block_begin_ = __ CatchBlockBegin();
805 return;
806 }
807
808 // Inserting the tagging in all of the predecessors.
809 auto predecessors = turboshaft_catch_handler->Predecessors();
810 turboshaft_catch_handler->ResetAllPredecessors();
811 base::SmallVector<V<Object>, 16> catch_block_begins;
812 for (Block* predecessor : predecessors) {
813 // Recording the CatchBlockBegin of this predecessor.
814 V<Object> catch_begin = predecessor->begin();
815 DCHECK(Asm().Get(catch_begin).template Is<CatchBlockBeginOp>());
816 catch_block_begins.push_back(catch_begin);
817
818 TagExceptionPhiInputsForBlock(predecessor, maglev_catch_handler,
819 turboshaft_catch_handler);
820 }
821
822 // Finally binding the catch handler.
823 __ Bind(turboshaft_catch_handler);
824
825 // We now need to insert a Phi for the CatchBlockBegins of the
826 // predecessors (usually, we would just call `__ CatchBlockbegin`, which
827 // takes care of creating a Phi node if necessary, but this won't work here,
828 // because this mechanisms expects the CatchBlockBegin to be the 1st
829 // instruction of the predecessors, and it isn't the case since the
830 // predecessors are now the blocks with the tagging).
831 catch_block_begin_ = __ Phi(base::VectorOf(catch_block_begins));
832 }
833 void TagExceptionPhiInputsForBlock(Block* old_block,
834 maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_catch_handler,
835 Block* turboshaft_catch_handler) {
836 DCHECK(maglev_catch_handler->has_phi());
837
838 // We start by patching in-place the predecessors final Goto of {old_block}
839 // to jump to a new block (in which we'll insert the tagging).
840 Block* new_block = __ NewBlock();
841 const GotoOp& old_goto =
842 old_block->LastOperation(__ output_graph()).Cast<GotoOp>();
843 DCHECK_EQ(old_goto.destination, turboshaft_catch_handler);
844 __ output_graph().Replace<GotoOp>(__ output_graph().Index(old_goto),
845 new_block, /* is_backedge */ false);
846 __ AddPredecessor(old_block, new_block, false);
847
848 // Now, we bind the new block and insert the taggings
849 __ BindReachable(new_block);
850 InsertTaggingForPhis(maglev_catch_handler);
851
852 // Finally, we just go from this block to the catch handler.
853 __ Goto(turboshaft_catch_handler);
854 }
855
856 void EmitLoopSinglePredecessorBlock(maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_loop_header) {
857 DCHECK(maglev_loop_header->is_loop());
858
859 bool has_special_generator_handling = false;
860 V<Word32> switch_var_first_input;
861 if (pre_loop_generator_blocks_.contains(maglev_loop_header)) {
862 // This loop header used to be bypassed by generator resume edges. It will
863 // now act as a secondary switch for the generator resumes.
864 std::vector<GeneratorSplitEdge>& generator_preds =
865 pre_loop_generator_blocks_[maglev_loop_header];
866 // {generator_preds} contains all of the edges that were bypassing this
867 // loop header. Rather than adding that many predecessors to the loop
868 // header, will create a single predecessor, {pred_for_generator}, to
869 // which all of the edges of {generator_preds} will go.
870 Block* pred_for_generator = __ NewBlock();
871
872 for (GeneratorSplitEdge pred : generator_preds) {
873 __ Bind(pred.pre_loop_dst);
874 __ SetVariable(header_switch_input_,
875 __ Word32Constant(pred.switch_value));
876 __ Goto(pred_for_generator);
877 }
878
879 __ Bind(pred_for_generator);
880 switch_var_first_input = __ GetVariable(header_switch_input_);
881 DCHECK(switch_var_first_input.valid());
882
883 BuildJump(maglev_loop_header);
884
885 has_special_generator_handling = true;
886 on_generator_switch_loop_ = true;
887 }
888
889 DCHECK(loop_single_edge_predecessors_.contains(maglev_loop_header));
890 Block* loop_pred = loop_single_edge_predecessors_[maglev_loop_header];
891 __ Bind(loop_pred);
892
893 if (maglev_loop_header->has_phi()) {
894 ComputePredecessorPermutations(maglev_loop_header, loop_pred, true,
895 has_special_generator_handling);
896
897 // Now we need to emit Phis (one per loop phi in {block}, which should
898 // contain the same input except for the backedge).
899 loop_phis_first_input_.clear();
900 loop_phis_first_input_index_ = 0;
901 for (maglev::Phi* phi : *maglev_loop_header->phis()) {
902 constexpr int kSkipBackedge = 1;
903 int input_count = phi->input_count() - kSkipBackedge;
904
905 if (has_special_generator_handling) {
906 // Adding an input to the Phis to account for the additional
907 // generator-related predecessor.
908 V<Any> additional_input;
909 switch (phi->value_representation()) {
910 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
911 additional_input = dummy_object_input_;
912 break;
913 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
914 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
915 additional_input = dummy_word32_input_;
916 break;
917 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
918 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
919 additional_input = dummy_float64_input_;
920 break;
921 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
922 // Maglev doesn't have IntPtr Phis.
923 UNREACHABLE();
924 }
925 loop_phis_first_input_.push_back(
926 MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(phi, input_count, additional_input));
927 } else {
928 loop_phis_first_input_.push_back(
929 MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(phi, input_count));
930 }
931 }
932 }
933
934 if (has_special_generator_handling) {
935 // We now emit the Phi that will be used in the loop's main switch.
936 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs;
937 constexpr int kSkipGeneratorPredecessor = 1;
938
939 // We insert a default input for all of the non-generator predecessor.
940 int input_count_without_generator =
941 loop_pred->PredecessorCount() - kSkipGeneratorPredecessor;
942 DCHECK(loop_default_generator_value_.valid());
943 inputs.insert(inputs.begin(), input_count_without_generator,
944 loop_default_generator_value_);
945
946 // And we insert the "true" input for the generator predecessor (which is
947 // {pred_for_generator} above).
948 DCHECK(switch_var_first_input.valid());
949 inputs.push_back(switch_var_first_input);
950
951 __ SetVariable(
952 header_switch_input_,
953 __ Phi(base::VectorOf(inputs), RegisterRepresentation::Word32()));
954 }
955
956 // Actually jumping to the loop.
957 __ Goto(Map(maglev_loop_header));
958 }
959
960 void PostPhiProcessing() {
961 // Loop headers that are bypassed because of generators need to be turned
962 // into secondary generator switches (so as to not be bypassed anymore).
963 // Concretely, we split the loop headers in half by inserting a Switch right
964 // after the loop phis have been emitted. Here is a visual representation of
965 // what's happening:
966 //
967 // Before:
968 //
969 // | ----------------------------
970 // | | |
971 // | | |
972 // v v |
973 // +------------------------+ |
974 // | phi_1(...) | |
975 // | ... | |
976 // | phi_k(...) | |
977 // | <some op 1> | |
978 // | ... | |
979 // | <some op n> | |
980 // | Branch | |
981 // +------------------------+ |
982 // | |
983 // | |
984 // v |
985 //
986 //
987 // After:
988 //
989 //
990 // | -----------------------------------
991 // | | |
992 // | | |
993 // v v |
994 // +------------------------+ |
995 // | phi_1(...) | |
996 // | ... | |
997 // | phi_k(...) | |
998 // | Switch | |
999 // +------------------------+ |
1000 // / | | \ |
1001 // / | | \ |
1002 // / | | \ |
1003 // v v v v |
1004 // +------------------+ |
1005 // | <some op 1> | |
1006 // | ... | |
1007 // | <some op n> | |
1008 // | Branch | |
1009 // +------------------+ |
1010 // | |
1011 // | |
1012 // v |
1013 //
1014 //
1015 // Since `PostPhiProcessing` is called right after all phis have been
1016 // emitted, now is thus the time to split the loop header.
1017
1018 if (on_generator_switch_loop_) {
1019 const maglev::BasicBlock* maglev_loop_header = __ maglev_input_block();
1020 DCHECK(maglev_loop_header->is_loop());
1021 std::vector<GeneratorSplitEdge>& generator_preds =
1022 pre_loop_generator_blocks_[maglev_loop_header];
1023
1024 compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
1025 __ output_graph().graph_zone()
1026 -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
1027 generator_preds.size());
1028
1029 for (int i = 0; static_cast<unsigned int>(i) < generator_preds.size();
1030 i++) {
1031 GeneratorSplitEdge pred = generator_preds[i];
1032 cases[i] = {pred.switch_value, pred.inside_loop_target,
1033 BranchHint::kNone};
1034 }
1035 Block* default_block = __ NewBlock();
1036 __ Switch(__ GetVariable(header_switch_input_),
1037 base::VectorOf(cases, generator_preds.size()), default_block);
1038
1039 // We now bind {default_block}. It will contain the rest of the loop
1040 // header. The MaglevGraphProcessor will continue to visit the header's
1041 // body as if nothing happened.
1042 __ Bind(default_block);
1043 }
1044 on_generator_switch_loop_ = false;
1045 }

1049 SetMap(node, __ HeapConstant(node->object().object()));

1091 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::InitialValue* node,
1092 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1093 // TODO(dmercadier): InitialValues are much simpler in Maglev because they
1094 // are mapped directly to interpreter registers, whereas Turbofan changes
1095 // the indices, making everything more complex. We should try to have the
1096 // same InitialValues in Turboshaft as in Maglev, in order to simplify
1097 // things.
1098#ifdef DEBUG
1099 // We cannot use strdup or something that simple for {debug_name}, because
1100 // it has to be zone allocated rather than heap-allocated, since it won't be
1101 // freed and this would thus cause a leak.
1102 std::string reg_string_name = node->source().ToString();
1103 base::Vector<char> debug_name_arr =
1104 graph_zone()->NewVector<char>(reg_string_name.length() + /* \n */ 1);
1105 snprintf(debug_name_arr.data(), debug_name_arr.length(), "%s",
1106 reg_string_name.c_str());
1107 char* debug_name = debug_name_arr.data();
1108#else
1109 char* debug_name = nullptr;
1110#endif
1111 interpreter::Register source = node->source();
1112 V<Object> value;
1113 if (source.is_function_closure()) {
1114 // The function closure is a Parameter rather than an OsrValue even when
1115 // OSR-compiling.
1116 value = __ Parameter(Linkage::kJSCallClosureParamIndex,
1117 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), debug_name);
1118 } else if (maglev_compilation_unit_->is_osr()) {
1119 int index;
1120 if (source.is_current_context()) {
1121 index = Linkage::kOsrContextSpillSlotIndex;
1122 } else if (source == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1123 index = Linkage::kOsrAccumulatorRegisterIndex;
1124 } else if (source.is_parameter()) {
1125 index = source.ToParameterIndex();
1126 } else {
1127 // For registers, recreate the index computed by FillWithOsrValues in
1128 // BytecodeGraphBuilder.
1129 index = source.index() + InterpreterFrameConstants::kExtraSlotCount +
1130 maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count();
1131 }
1132 value = __ OsrValue(index);
1133 } else {
1134 int index = source.ToParameterIndex();
1135 if (source.is_current_context()) {
1136 index = Linkage::GetJSCallContextParamIndex(
1137 maglev_compilation_unit_->parameter_count());
1138 } else {
1139 index = source.ToParameterIndex();
1140 }
1141 value = __ Parameter(index, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), debug_name);
1142 }
1143 SetMap(node, value);
1144 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1145 }
1146 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::RegisterInput* node,
1147 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1148 DCHECK(maglev_compilation_unit_->bytecode()
1149 .incoming_new_target_or_generator_register()
1150 .is_valid());
1151 DCHECK_EQ(node->input(), kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister);
1152 DCHECK(new_target_param_.valid());
1153 SetMap(node, new_target_param_);
1154 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1155 }
1156
1157 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::FunctionEntryStackCheck* node,
1158 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1159 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1160 __ JSFunctionEntryStackCheck(native_context(), frame_state);
1161 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1162 }
1163
1164 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Phi* node,
1165 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1166 int input_count = node->input_count();
1167 RegisterRepresentation rep =
1168 RegisterRepresentationFor(node->value_representation());
1169 if (node->is_exception_phi()) {
1170 if (node->owner() == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
1171 DCHECK(catch_block_begin_.valid());
1172 SetMap(node, catch_block_begin_);
1173 } else {
1174 Variable var = regs_to_vars_[node->owner().index()];
1175 SetMap(node, __ GetVariable(var));
1176 // {var} won't be used anymore once we've created the mapping from
1177 // {node} to its value. We thus reset it, in order to avoid Phis being
1178 // created for {var} at later merge points.
1179 __ SetVariable(var, V<Object>::Invalid());
1180 }
1181 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1182 }
1183 if (__ current_block()->IsLoop()) {
1184 DCHECK(state.block()->is_loop());
1185 OpIndex first_phi_input;
1186 if (state.block()->predecessor_count() > 2 ||
1187 generator_analyzer_.HeaderIsBypassed(state.block())) {
1188 // This loop has multiple forward edges in Maglev, so we should have
1189 // created an intermediate block in Turboshaft, which will be the only
1190 // predecessor of the Turboshaft loop, and from which we'll find the
1191 // first input for this loop phi.
1192 DCHECK_EQ(loop_phis_first_input_.size(),
1193 static_cast<size_t>(state.block()->phis()->LengthForTest()));
1194 DCHECK_GE(loop_phis_first_input_index_, 0);
1195 DCHECK_LT(loop_phis_first_input_index_, loop_phis_first_input_.size());
1196 DCHECK(loop_single_edge_predecessors_.contains(state.block()));
1197 DCHECK_EQ(loop_single_edge_predecessors_[state.block()],
1198 __ current_block()->LastPredecessor());
1199 first_phi_input = loop_phis_first_input_[loop_phis_first_input_index_];
1200 loop_phis_first_input_index_++;
1201 } else {
1202 DCHECK_EQ(input_count, 2);
1203 DCHECK_EQ(state.block()->predecessor_count(), 2);
1204 DCHECK(loop_phis_first_input_.empty());
1205 first_phi_input = Map(node->input(0));
1206 }
1207 SetMap(node, __ PendingLoopPhi(first_phi_input, rep));
1208 } else {
1209 SetMap(node, MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(node, input_count));
1210 }
1211 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1212 }
1213
1214 V<Any> MakePhiMaybePermuteInputs(
1215 maglev::ValueNode* maglev_node, int maglev_input_count,
1216 OptionalV<Any> additional_input = OptionalV<Any>::Nullopt()) {
1217 DCHECK(!predecessor_permutation_.empty());
1218
1219 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> inputs;
1220 // Note that it's important to use `current_block()->PredecessorCount()` as
1221 // the size of {inputs}, because some Maglev predecessors could have been
1222 // dropped by Turboshaft during the translation (and thus, `input_count`
1223 // might be too much).
1224 inputs.resize_and_init(__ current_block()->PredecessorCount());
1225 for (int i = 0; i < maglev_input_count; ++i) {
1226 if (predecessor_permutation_[i] != Block::kInvalidPredecessorIndex) {
1227 inputs[predecessor_permutation_[i]] =
1228 MapPhiInput(maglev_node->input(i), predecessor_permutation_[i]);
1229 }
1230 }
1231
1232 if (additional_input.has_value()) {
1233 // When a loop header was bypassed by a generator resume, we insert an
1234 // additional predecessor to the loop, and thus need an additional input
1235 // for the Phis.
1236 inputs[inputs.size() - 1] = additional_input.value();
1237 }
1238
1239 return __ Phi(
1240 base::VectorOf(inputs),
1241 RegisterRepresentationFor(maglev_node->value_representation()));
1242 }
1243
1244 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Call* node,
1245 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1246 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1247 V<Object> function = Map(node->function());
1248 V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1249
1250 Builtin builtin;
1251 switch (node->target_type()) {
1252 case maglev::Call::TargetType::kAny:
1253 switch (node->receiver_mode()) {
1254 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
1255 builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined;
1256 break;
1257 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
1258 builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined;
1259 break;
1260 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
1261 builtin = Builtin::kCall_ReceiverIsAny;
1262 break;
1263 }
1264 break;
1265 case maglev::Call::TargetType::kJSFunction:
1266 switch (node->receiver_mode()) {
1267 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNullOrUndefined:
1268 builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNullOrUndefined;
1269 break;
1270 case ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined:
1271 builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsNotNullOrUndefined;
1272 break;
1273 case ConvertReceiverMode::kAny:
1274 builtin = Builtin::kCallFunction_ReceiverIsAny;
1275 break;
1276 }
1277 break;
1278 }
1279
1280 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1281 arguments.push_back(function);
1282 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1283 for (auto arg : node->args()) {
1284 arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1285 }
1286 arguments.push_back(context);
1287
1288 GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state,
1289 base::VectorOf(arguments), node->num_args());
1290
1291 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1292 }
1293 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallKnownJSFunction* node,
1294 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1295 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1296 V<Object> callee = Map(node->closure());
1297 int actual_parameter_count = JSParameterCount(node->num_args());
1298
1299 if (node->shared_function_info().HasBuiltinId()) {
1300 // Note that there is no need for a ThrowingScope here:
1301 // GenerateBuiltinCall takes care of creating one.
1302 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1303 arguments.push_back(callee);
1304 arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1305 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(actual_parameter_count));
1306#ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
1307 arguments.push_back(
1308 __ Word32Constant(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value()));
1309#endif
1310 arguments.push_back(Map(node->receiver()));
1311 for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
1312 arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
1313 }
1314 // Setting missing arguments to Undefined.
1315 for (int i = actual_parameter_count; i < node->expected_parameter_count();
1316 i++) {
1317 arguments.push_back(__ HeapConstant(local_factory_->undefined_value()));
1318 }
1319 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1320 GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(
1321 node, node->shared_function_info().builtin_id(), frame_state,
1322 base::VectorOf(arguments),
1323 std::max<int>(actual_parameter_count,
1324 node->expected_parameter_count()));
1325 } else {
1326 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1327 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1328 arguments.push_back(Map(node->receiver()));
1329 for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
1330 arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
1331 }
1332 // Setting missing arguments to Undefined.
1333 for (int i = actual_parameter_count; i < node->expected_parameter_count();
1334 i++) {
1335 arguments.push_back(__ HeapConstant(local_factory_->undefined_value()));
1336 }
1337 arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1338 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(actual_parameter_count));
1339#ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
1340 arguments.push_back(
1341 __ Word32Constant(kPlaceholderDispatchHandle.value()));
1342#endif
1343
1344 // Load the context from {callee}.
1345 OpIndex context =
1346 __ LoadField(callee, AccessBuilder::ForJSFunctionContext());
1347 arguments.push_back(context);
1348
1349 const CallDescriptor* descriptor = Linkage::GetJSCallDescriptor(
1350 graph_zone(), false,
1351 std::max<int>(actual_parameter_count,
1352 node->expected_parameter_count()),
1353 CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState | CallDescriptor::kCanUseRoots);
1354
1355 LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw = ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node);
1356
1357 BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size());
1358 SetMap(node, __ Call(V<CallTarget>::Cast(callee), frame_state,
1359 base::VectorOf(arguments),
1360 TSCallDescriptor::Create(descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
1361 lazy_deopt_on_throw,
1362 graph_zone())));
1363 }
1364
1365 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1366 }
1367 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallKnownApiFunction* node,
1368 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1369 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1370
1371 if (node->inline_builtin()) {
1372 DCHECK(v8_flags.maglev_inline_api_calls);
1373 // TODO(dmercadier, 40912714, 42203760): The flag maglev_inline_api_calls
1374 // is currently experimental, and it's not clear at this point if it will
1375 // even become non-experimental, so we currently don't support it in the
1376 // Maglev->Turboshaft translation. Note that a quick-fix would be to treat
1377 // kNoProfilingInlined like kNoProfiling, although this would be slower
1378 // than desired.
1379 UNIMPLEMENTED();
1380 }
1381
1382 OpIndex api_holder;
1383 if (node->api_holder().has_value()) {
1384 api_holder = __ HeapConstant(node->api_holder().value().object());
1385 } else {
1386 api_holder = Map(node->receiver());
1387 }
1388
1389 V<Object> target =
1390 __ HeapConstant(node->function_template_info().AsHeapObject().object());
1391
1392 ApiFunction function(node->function_template_info().callback(broker_));
1393 ExternalReference function_ref = ExternalReference::Create(
1394 &function, ExternalReference::DIRECT_API_CALL);
1395
1396 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1397 arguments.push_back(__ ExternalConstant(function_ref));
1398 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1399 arguments.push_back(target);
1400 arguments.push_back(api_holder);
1401 arguments.push_back(Map(node->receiver()));
1402 for (maglev::Input arg : node->args()) {
1403 arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1404 }
1405 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1406
1407 Builtin builtin;
1408 switch (node->mode()) {
1409 case maglev::CallKnownApiFunction::Mode::kNoProfiling:
1410 builtin = Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimizedNoProfiling;
1411 break;
1412 case maglev::CallKnownApiFunction::Mode::kNoProfilingInlined:
1413 // Handled earlier when checking `node->inline_builtin()`.
1414 UNREACHABLE();
1415 case maglev::CallKnownApiFunction::Mode::kGeneric:
1416 builtin = Builtin::kCallApiCallbackOptimized;
1417 break;
1418 }
1419
1420 int stack_arg_count = node->num_args() + /* implicit receiver */ 1;
1421 GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state,
1422 base::VectorOf(arguments), stack_arg_count);
1423
1424 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1425 }
1426 V<Any> GenerateBuiltinCall(
1427 maglev::NodeBase* node, Builtin builtin,
1428 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state, base::Vector<const OpIndex> arguments,
1429 std::optional<int> stack_arg_count = std::nullopt) {
1430 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1431 DCHECK(!TooManyArgumentsForCall(arguments.size()));
1432
1433 Callable callable = Builtins::CallableFor(isolate_, builtin);
1434 const CallInterfaceDescriptor& descriptor = callable.descriptor();
1435 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetStubCallDescriptor(
1436 graph_zone(), descriptor,
1437 stack_arg_count.has_value() ? stack_arg_count.value()
1438 : descriptor.GetStackParameterCount(),
1439 frame_state.valid() ? CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState
1440 : CallDescriptor::kNoFlags);
1441 V<Code> stub_code = __ HeapConstant(callable.code());
1442
1443 LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw = ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node);
1444
1445 return __ Call(stub_code, frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
1446 TSCallDescriptor::Create(call_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
1447 lazy_deopt_on_throw, graph_zone()));
1448 }
1449 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallBuiltin* node,
1450 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1451 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1452
1453 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1454 for (int i = 0; i < node->InputCountWithoutContext(); i++) {
1455 arguments.push_back(Map(node->input(i)));
1456 }
1457
1458 if (node->has_feedback()) {
1459 V<Any> feedback_slot;
1460 switch (node->slot_type()) {
1461 case maglev::CallBuiltin::kTaggedIndex:
1462 feedback_slot = __ TaggedIndexConstant(node->feedback().index());
1463 break;
1464 case maglev::CallBuiltin::kSmi:
1465 feedback_slot = __ WordPtrConstant(node->feedback().index());
1466 break;
1467 }
1468 arguments.push_back(feedback_slot);
1469 arguments.push_back(__ HeapConstant(node->feedback().vector));
1470 }
1471
1472 auto descriptor = Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(node->builtin());
1473 if (descriptor.HasContextParameter()) {
1474 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context_input()));
1475 }
1476
1477 int stack_arg_count =
1478 node->InputCountWithoutContext() - node->InputsInRegisterCount();
1479 if (node->has_feedback()) {
1480 // We might need to take the feedback slot and vector into account for
1481 // {stack_arg_count}. There are three possibilities:
1482 // 1. Feedback slot and vector are in register.
1483 // 2. Feedback slot is in register and vector is on stack.
1484 // 3. Feedback slot and vector are on stack.
1485 int slot_index = node->InputCountWithoutContext();
1486 int vector_index = slot_index + 1;
1487 if (vector_index < descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
1488 // stack_arg_count is already correct.
1489 } else if (vector_index == descriptor.GetRegisterParameterCount()) {
1490 // feedback vector is on the stack
1491 stack_arg_count += 1;
1492 } else {
1493 // feedback slot and vector on the stack
1494 stack_arg_count += 2;
1495 }
1496 }
1497
1498 BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size());
1499 V<Any> call_idx =
1500 GenerateBuiltinCall(node, node->builtin(), frame_state,
1501 base::VectorOf(arguments), stack_arg_count);
1502 SetMapMaybeMultiReturn(node, call_idx);
1503
1504 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1505 }
1506 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallRuntime* node,
1507 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1508 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1509 LazyDeoptOnThrow lazy_deopt_on_throw = ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node);
1510
1511 auto c_entry_stub = __ CEntryStubConstant(isolate_, node->ReturnCount());
1512
1513 CallDescriptor* call_descriptor = Linkage::GetRuntimeCallDescriptor(
1514 graph_zone(), node->function_id(), node->num_args(),
1515 Operator::kNoProperties, CallDescriptor::kNeedsFrameState,
1516 lazy_deopt_on_throw);
1517
1518 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1519 for (int i = 0; i < node->num_args(); i++) {
1520 arguments.push_back(Map(node->arg(i)));
1521 }
1522
1523 arguments.push_back(
1524 __ ExternalConstant(ExternalReference::Create(node->function_id())));
1525 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1526
1527 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1528
1529 OptionalV<FrameState> frame_state = OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
1530 if (call_descriptor->NeedsFrameState()) {
1531 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state_value, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1532 frame_state = frame_state_value;
1533 }
1534 DCHECK_IMPLIES(lazy_deopt_on_throw == LazyDeoptOnThrow::kYes,
1535 frame_state.has_value());
1536
1537 BAILOUT_IF_TOO_MANY_ARGUMENTS_FOR_CALL(arguments.size());
1538 V<Any> call_idx =
1539 __ Call(c_entry_stub, frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
1540 TSCallDescriptor::Create(call_descriptor, CanThrow::kYes,
1541 lazy_deopt_on_throw, graph_zone()));
1542 SetMapMaybeMultiReturn(node, call_idx);
1543
1544 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1545 }

1547 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ThrowReferenceErrorIfHole* node,
1548 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1549 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1550
1551 IF (UNLIKELY(RootEqual(node->value(), RootIndex::kTheHoleValue))) {
1552 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1553 __ CallRuntime_ThrowAccessedUninitializedVariable(
1554 isolate_, frame_state, native_context(), ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node),
1555 __ HeapConstant(node->name().object()));
1556 // TODO(dmercadier): use RuntimeAbort here instead of Unreachable.
1557 // However, before doing so, RuntimeAbort should be changed so that 1)
1558 // it's a block terminator and 2) it doesn't call the runtime when
1559 // v8_flags.trap_on_abort is true.
1560 __ Unreachable();
1561 }
1562 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1563 }

1566 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {

1578 isolate_, frame_state, native_context(), ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node),
1579 constructor, Map(node->function()));

1581 // However, before doing so, RuntimeAbort should be changed so that 1)
1582 // it's a block terminator and 2) it doesn't call the runtime when
1583 // v8_flags.trap_on_abort is true.
1584 __ Unreachable();
1585 }
1586
1587 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1588 }

1752 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CallForwardVarargs* node,
1753 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1754 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
1755
1756 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1757 V<JSFunction> function = Map(node->function());
1758 V<Context> context = Map(node->context());
1759
1760 base::SmallVector<V<Object>, 16> arguments;
1761 for (auto arg : node->args()) {
1762 arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1763 }
1764 DCHECK_EQ(node->num_args(), arguments.size());
1765
1766 Builtin builtin;
1767 switch (node->target_type()) {
1768 case maglev::Call::TargetType::kJSFunction:
1769 builtin = Builtin::kCallFunctionForwardVarargs;
1770 break;
1771 case maglev::Call::TargetType::kAny:
1772 builtin = Builtin::kCallForwardVarargs;
1773 break;
1774 }
1775 V<Object> call = __ CallBuiltin_CallForwardVarargs(
1776 isolate_, graph_zone(), builtin, frame_state, context, function,
1777 node->num_args(), node->start_index(), base::VectorOf(arguments),
1778 ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node));

1780 SetMap(node, call);
1781 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

1783
1784 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Construct* node,
1785 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1786 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1787 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1788
1789 arguments.push_back(Map(node->function()));
1790 arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1791 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args()));
1792
1793#ifndef V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
1794 arguments.push_back(__ WordPtrConstant(node->feedback().index()));
1795 arguments.push_back(__ HeapConstant(node->feedback().vector));
1796#endif
1797
1798 for (auto arg : node->args()) {
1799 arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1800 }
1801
1802 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1803
1804#ifndef V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
1805 // Construct_WithFeedback can't be called from Turbofan on Arm64, because of
1806 // the stack alignment requirements: the feedback vector is dropped by
1807 // Construct_WithFeedback while the other arguments are passed through to
1808 // Construct. As a result, when the feedback vector is pushed on the stack,
1809 // it should be padded to 16-bytes, but there is no way to express this in
1810 // Turbofan.
1811 // Anyways, long-term we'll want to feedback-specialize Construct in the
1812 // frontend (ie, probably in Maglev), so we don't really need to adapt
1813 // Turbofan to be able to call Construct_WithFeedback on Arm64.
1814 static constexpr int kFeedbackVector = 1;
1815 int stack_arg_count = node->num_args() + kFeedbackVector;
1816 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kConstruct_WithFeedback;
1817#else
1818 int stack_arg_count = node->num_args();
1819 Builtin builtin = Builtin::kConstruct;
1820#endif
1821
1822 GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, builtin, frame_state,
1823 base::VectorOf(arguments), stack_arg_count);
1824
1825 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1826 }
1827 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ConstructWithSpread* node,
1828 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
1829 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
1830
1831 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> arguments;
1832 arguments.push_back(Map(node->function()));
1833 arguments.push_back(Map(node->new_target()));
1834 arguments.push_back(__ Word32Constant(node->num_args_no_spread()));
1835 arguments.push_back(Map(node->spread()));
1836
1837 for (auto arg : node->args_no_spread()) {
1838 arguments.push_back(Map(arg));
1839 }
1840
1841 arguments.push_back(Map(node->context()));
1842
1843 GENERATE_AND_MAP_BUILTIN_CALL(node, Builtin::kConstructWithSpread,
1844 frame_state, base::VectorOf(arguments),
1845 node->num_args_no_spread());
1846 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1847 }

1851 Map(node->implicit_receiver_input())));
1852 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
1853 }

2238 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckNumber* node,

2241 V<Object> input = Map(node->receiver_input());

2250 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());

2261 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedNumberToInt32* node,
2262 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2263 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2264 V<Object> input = Map(node->input());

2266 IF (__ IsSmi(input)) {
2267 value = __ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(input));
2268 } ELSE {
2269 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ IsHeapNumberMap(__ LoadMapField(input)),
2270 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32,
2271 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2272 value = __ ChangeFloat64ToInt32OrDeopt(
2273 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(input)), frame_state,
2274 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero,
2275 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());

2277 SetMap(node, value);
2278 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

2288 void CheckMaps(V<Object> receiver_input, V<FrameState> frame_state,
2289 OptionalV<Map> object_map, const FeedbackSource& feedback,
2290 const compiler::ZoneRefSet<Map>& maps, bool check_heap_object,
2291 CheckMapsFlags flags) {
2292 Label<> done(this);
2293 if (check_heap_object) {
2294 OpIndex is_smi = __ IsSmi(receiver_input);
2295 if (AnyMapIsHeapNumber(maps)) {
2296 // Smis count as matching the HeapNumber map, so we're done.
2297 GOTO_IF(is_smi, done);
2298 } else {
2299 __ DeoptimizeIf(is_smi, frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kWrongMap,
2300 feedback);
2301 }
2302 }
2303
2304#ifdef DEBUG
2305 if (flags & CheckMapsFlag::kTryMigrateInstance) {
2306 bool has_migration_targets = false;
2307 for (MapRef map : maps) {
2308 if (map.object()->is_migration_target()) {
2309 has_migration_targets = true;
2310 break;
2311 }
2312 }
2313 DCHECK(has_migration_targets);
2314 }
2315#endif // DEBUG
2316
2317 __ CheckMaps(V<HeapObject>::Cast(receiver_input), frame_state, object_map,
2318 maps, flags, feedback);
2319
2320 if (done.has_incoming_jump()) {
2321 GOTO(done);
2322 BIND(done);
2323 }
2324 }
2325 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckMaps* node,
2326 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2327 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2328 CheckMaps(Map(node->receiver_input()), frame_state, {},
2329 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update(),
2330 node->maps().Clone(graph_zone()),
2331 node->check_type() == maglev::CheckType::kCheckHeapObject,
2332 CheckMapsFlag::kNone);
2333 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2334 }
2335 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckMapsWithAlreadyLoadedMap* node,
2336 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2337 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2338 CheckMaps(Map(node->object_input()), frame_state, Map(node->map_input()),
2339 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update(),
2340 node->maps().Clone(graph_zone()), /*check_heap_object*/ false,
2341 CheckMapsFlag::kNone);

2478 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckInt32Condition* node,
2479 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2480 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2481 bool negate_result = false;
2482 V<Word32> cmp = ConvertInt32Compare(node->left_input(), node->right_input(),
2483 node->condition(), &negate_result);
2484 if (negate_result) {
2485 __ DeoptimizeIf(cmp, frame_state, node->reason(),
2486 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2487 } else {
2488 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(cmp, frame_state, node->reason(),
2489 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2490 }
2491 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2492 }

2494 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::AllocationBlock* node,
2495 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2496 DCHECK(
2497 node->is_used()); // Should have been dead-code eliminated otherwise.
2498 int size = 0;
2499 for (auto alloc : node->allocation_list()) {
2500 if (!alloc->HasBeenAnalysed() || alloc->HasEscaped()) {
2501 alloc->set_offset(size);
2502 size += alloc->size();
2503 }
2504 }
2505 node->set_size(size);
2506 SetMap(node, __ FinishInitialization(
2507 __ Allocate<HeapObject>(size, node->allocation_type())));
2508 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2509 }
2510 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::InlinedAllocation* node,
2511 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2512 DCHECK(node->HasBeenAnalysed() &&
2513 node->HasEscaped()); // Would have been removed otherwise.
2514 V<HeapObject> alloc = Map(node->allocation_block());
2515 SetMap(node, __ BitcastWordPtrToHeapObject(__ WordPtrAdd(
2516 __ BitcastHeapObjectToWordPtr(alloc), node->offset())));
2517 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2518 }

2599 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
2600 RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE();
2601
2602 SetMap(node,

2604 NewArrayOp::Kind::kObject, node->allocation_type()));

2608 template <typename Node>
2609 maglev::ProcessResult StringConcatHelper(Node* node, V<String> left,
2610 V<String> right) {
2611 // When coming from Turbofan, StringConcat is always guarded by a check that
2612 // the length is less than String::kMaxLength, which prevents StringConcat
2613 // from ever throwing (and as a consequence of this, it does not need a
2614 // Context input). This is not the case for Maglev. To mimic Turbofan's
2615 // behavior, we thus insert here a length check.
2616 // TODO(dmercadier): I'm not convinced that these checks make a lot of
2617 // sense, since they make the graph bigger, and throwing before the builtin
2618 // call to StringConcat isn't super important since throwing is not supposed
2619 // to be fast. We should consider just calling the builtin and letting it
2620 // throw. With LazyDeopOnThrow, this is currently a bit verbose to
2621 // implement, so we should first find a way to have this LazyDeoptOnThrow
2622 // without adding a member to all throwing operations (like adding
2623 // LazyDeoptOnThrow in FrameStateOp).
2624 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
2625
2626 V<Word32> left_len = __ StringLength(left);
2627 V<Word32> right_len = __ StringLength(right);
2628
2629 V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> len_and_ovf =
2630 __ Int32AddCheckOverflow(left_len, right_len);
2631 V<Word32> len = __ Projection<0>(len_and_ovf);
2632 V<Word32> ovf = __ Projection<1>(len_and_ovf);
2633
2634 Label<> throw_invalid_length(this);
2635 Label<> done(this);
2636
2637 GOTO_IF(UNLIKELY(ovf), throw_invalid_length);
2638 GOTO_IF(LIKELY(__ Uint32LessThanOrEqual(len, String::kMaxLength)), done);
2639
2640 GOTO(throw_invalid_length);
2641 BIND(throw_invalid_length);
2642 {
2643 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
2644 __ CallRuntime_ThrowInvalidStringLength(isolate_, frame_state,
2645 native_context(),
2646 ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node));
2647 // We should not return from Throw.
2648 __ Unreachable();
2649 }
2650
2651 BIND(done);
2652 SetMap(node, __ StringConcat(__ TagSmi(len), left, right));
2653 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2654 }
2655 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::StringConcat* node,
2656 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2657 V<String> left = Map(node->lhs());
2658 V<String> right = Map(node->rhs());
2659 return StringConcatHelper(node, left, right);
2660 }
2661 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::StringWrapperConcat* node,
2662 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2663 V<HeapObject> left_string_or_wrapper = Map(node->lhs());
2664 V<HeapObject> right_string_or_wrapper = Map(node->rhs());
2665
2666 ScopedVar<String, AssemblerT> left(this);
2667 ScopedVar<String, AssemblerT> right(this);
2668 IF (__ ObjectIsString(left_string_or_wrapper)) {
2669 left = V<String>::Cast(left_string_or_wrapper);
2670 } ELSE {
2671 left = V<String>::Cast(__ LoadTaggedField(
2672 V<JSPrimitiveWrapper>::Cast(left_string_or_wrapper),
2673 JSPrimitiveWrapper::kValueOffset));
2674 }
2675 IF (__ ObjectIsString(right_string_or_wrapper)) {
2676 right = V<String>::Cast(right_string_or_wrapper);
2677 } ELSE {
2678 right = V<String>::Cast(__ LoadTaggedField(
2679 V<JSPrimitiveWrapper>::Cast(right_string_or_wrapper),
2680 JSPrimitiveWrapper::kValueOffset));
2681 }
2682
2683 return StringConcatHelper(node, left, right);
2684 }

2743 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ToString* node,
2744 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2745 ThrowingScope throwing_scope(this, node);
2746
2747 Label<String> done(this);
2748
2749 V<Object> value = Map(node->value_input());
2750 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->lazy_deopt_info());
2751
2752 GOTO_IF(__ ObjectIsString(value), done, V<String>::Cast(value));
2753
2754 IF_NOT (__ IsSmi(value)) {
2755 if (node->mode() == maglev::ToString::ConversionMode::kConvertSymbol) {
2756 V<i::Map> map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2757 V<Word32> instance_type = __ LoadInstanceTypeField(map);
2758 IF (__ Word32Equal(instance_type, SYMBOL_TYPE)) {
2759 GOTO(done, __ CallRuntime_SymbolDescriptiveString(
2760 isolate_, frame_state, Map(node->context()),
2761 V<Symbol>::Cast(value), ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node)));
2762 }
2763 }
2764 }
2765
2766 GOTO(done,
2767 __ CallBuiltin_ToString(isolate_, frame_state, Map(node->context()),
2768 value, ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node)));
2769
2770 BIND(done, result);
2771 SetMap(node, result);
2772 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2773 }
2774 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::NumberToString* node,
2775 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2776 NoThrowingScopeRequired no_throws(node);
2777
2778 SetMap(node,
2779 __ CallBuiltin_NumberToString(isolate_, Map(node->value_input())));
2780 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2781 }

2805 template <typename T>
2806 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::AbstractLoadTaggedField<T>* node,
2807 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2808 V<Object> value =
2809 __ LoadTaggedField(Map(node->object_input()), node->offset());
2810 SetMap(node, value);
2811
2812 if (generator_analyzer_.has_header_bypasses() &&
2813 maglev_generator_context_node_ == nullptr &&
2814 node->object_input().node()->template Is<maglev::RegisterInput>() &&
2815 node->offset() == JSGeneratorObject::kContextOffset) {
2816 // This is loading the context of a generator for the 1st time. We save it
2817 // in {generator_context_} for later use.
2818 __ SetVariable(generator_context_, value);
2819 maglev_generator_context_node_ = node;
2820 }
2821
2822 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2823 }
2824 maglev::ProcessResult Process(
2825 maglev::LoadTaggedFieldForScriptContextSlot* node,
2826 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2827 V<Context> script_context = V<Context>::Cast(Map(node->context()));
2828 V<Object> value = __ LoadTaggedField(script_context, node->offset());
2829 ScopedVar<Object, AssemblerT> result(this, value);
2830 IF_NOT (__ IsSmi(value)) {
2831 V<i::Map> value_map = __ LoadMapField(value);
2832 IF (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
2833 value_map, __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->heap_number_map())))) {
2834 V<HeapNumber> heap_number = V<HeapNumber>::Cast(value);
2835 result = __ LoadHeapNumberFromScriptContext(script_context,
2836 node->index(), heap_number);
2837 }
2838 }
2839 SetMap(node, result);
2840 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2841 }
2842 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadDoubleField* node,
2843 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2844 V<HeapNumber> field = __ LoadTaggedField<HeapNumber>(
2845 Map(node->object_input()), node->offset());
2846 SetMap(node, __ LoadHeapNumberValue(field));
2847 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2848 }
2849 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadFloat64* node,
2850 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2851 SetMap(node, __ Load(Map(node->object_input()), LoadOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
2852 MemoryRepresentation::Float64(), node->offset()));

2919 maglev::ProcessResult Process(
2920 maglev::StoreScriptContextSlotWithWriteBarrier* node,
2921 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
2922 Label<> done(this);
2923 V<Context> context = V<i::Context>::Cast(Map(node->context_input()));
2924 V<Object> new_value = Map(node->new_value_input());
2925 V<Object> old_value = __ LoadTaggedField(context, node->offset());
2926 IF_NOT (__ TaggedEqual(old_value, new_value)) {
2927 V<Object> side_data =
2928 __ LoadScriptContextSideData(context, node->index());
2929 IF_NOT (UNLIKELY(__ TaggedEqual(
2930 side_data,
2931 __ SmiConstant(ContextSidePropertyCell::Other())))) {
2932 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
2933 __ StoreScriptContextSlowPath(
2934 context, old_value, new_value, side_data, frame_state,
2935 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update(), done);
2936 }
2937 __ Store(context, new_value, StoreOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
2938 MemoryRepresentation::AnyTagged(),
2939 WriteBarrierKind::kFullWriteBarrier, node->offset(), false);
2940 }
2941 GOTO(done);
2942 BIND(done);
2943 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
2944 }

3024 __ LoadField<Word32>(V<i::Map>::Cast(Map(node->map_input())),
3025 AccessBuilder::ForMapBitField3());
3026 V<Word32> length = __ Word32ShiftRightLogical(
3027 __ Word32BitwiseAnd(bitfield3, Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kMask),
3028 Map::Bits3::EnumLengthBits::kShift);
3029 SetMap(node, length);

3032 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckCacheIndicesNotCleared* node,
3033 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3034 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
3035 // If the cache length is zero, we don't have any indices, so we know this
3036 // is ok even though the indices are the empty array.
3037 IF_NOT (__ Word32Equal(Map(node->length_input()), 0)) {
3038 // Otherwise, an empty array with non-zero required length is not valid.
3039 V<Word32> condition =
3040 RootEqual(node->indices_input(), RootIndex::kEmptyFixedArray);
3041 __ DeoptimizeIf(condition, frame_state,
3042 DeoptimizeReason::kWrongEnumIndices,
3043 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
3044 }
3045 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3046 }

3055 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::LoadTypedArrayLength* node,
3056 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3057 // TODO(dmercadier): consider loading the raw length instead of the byte
3058 // length. This is not currently done because the raw length field might be
3059 // removed soon.
3060 V<WordPtr> length =
3061 __ LoadField<WordPtr>(Map<JSTypedArray>(node->receiver_input()),
3062 AccessBuilder::ForJSTypedArrayByteLength());
3063
3064 int shift_size = ElementsKindToShiftSize(node->elements_kind());
3065 if (shift_size > 0) {
3066 DCHECK(shift_size == 1 || shift_size == 2 || shift_size == 3);
3067 length = __ WordPtrShiftRightLogical(length, shift_size);
3068 }
3069 SetMap(node, length);
3070 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

3132
3133 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckJSDataViewBounds* node,
3134 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3135 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
3136 // Normal DataView (backed by AB / SAB) or non-length tracking backed by
3137 // GSAB.
3138 V<WordPtr> byte_length =
3139 __ LoadField<WordPtr>(Map<JSTypedArray>(node->receiver_input()),
3140 AccessBuilder::ForJSDataViewByteLength());
3141
3142 int element_size = ExternalArrayElementSize(node->element_type());
3143 if (element_size > 1) {
3144 // For element_size larger than 1, we need to make sure that {index} is
3145 // less than {byte_length}, but also that {index+element_size} is less
3146 // than {byte_length}. We do this by subtracting {element_size-1} from
3147 // {byte_length}: if the resulting length is greater than 0, then we can
3148 // just treat {element_size} as 1 and check if {index} is less than this
3149 // new {byte_length}.
3150 DCHECK(element_size == 2 || element_size == 4 || element_size == 8);
3151 byte_length = __ WordPtrSub(byte_length, element_size - 1);
3152 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ IntPtrLessThan(byte_length, 0), frame_state,
3153 DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds,
3154 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
3155 }
3156 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
3157 __ Uint32LessThan(Map<Word32>(node->index_input()),
3158 __ TruncateWordPtrToWord32(byte_length)),
3159 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kOutOfBounds,
3160 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
3161 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3162 }

3172 SetMap(node, __ LoadDataViewElement(
3173 data_view, storage,

3175 is_little_endian, node->type()));

3234
3235 void BuildJump(maglev::BasicBlock* target) {
3236 Block* destination = Map(target);
3237 if (target->is_loop() && (target->predecessor_count() > 2 ||
3238 generator_analyzer_.HeaderIsBypassed(target))) {
3239 // This loop has multiple forward edges in Maglev, so we'll create an
3240 // extra block in Turboshaft that will be the only predecessor.
3241 auto it = loop_single_edge_predecessors_.find(target);
3242 if (it != loop_single_edge_predecessors_.end()) {
3243 destination = it->second;
3244 } else {
3245 Block* loop_only_pred = __ NewBlock();
3246 loop_single_edge_predecessors_[target] = loop_only_pred;
3247 destination = loop_only_pred;
3248 }
3249 }
3250 __ Goto(destination);
3251 }
3252
3253 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Jump* node,
3254 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3255 BuildJump(node->target());
3256 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3257 }
3258 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckpointedJump* node,
3259 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3260 BuildJump(node->target());
3261 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3262 }
3263
3264 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::JumpLoop* node,
3265 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3266 if (header_switch_input_.valid()) {
3267 __ SetVariable(header_switch_input_, loop_default_generator_value_);
3268 }
3269 __ Goto(Map(node->target()));
3270 FixLoopPhis(node->target());
3271 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3272 }
