3303 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TestUndetectable* node,
3304 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3305 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions assumption;
3306 switch (node->check_type()) {
3307 case maglev::CheckType::kCheckHeapObject:
3308 assumption = ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone;
3309 break;
3310 case maglev::CheckType::kOmitHeapObjectCheck:
3311 assumption = ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kHeapObject;
3312 break;
3313 }
3314 SetMap(node, ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3315 __ ObjectIs(Map(node->value()),
3316 ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable, assumption)));
3317 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3318 }
3319 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TestTypeOf* node,
3320 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3321 V<Object> input = Map(node->value());
3322 V<Boolean> result;
3323 switch (node->literal()) {
3324 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kNumber:
3325 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3326 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNumber,
3327 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3328 break;
3329 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kString:
3330 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3331 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kString,
3332 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3333 break;
3334 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kSymbol:
3335 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3336 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kSymbol,
3337 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3338 break;
3339 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kBigInt:
3340 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3341 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kBigInt,
3342 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3343 break;
3344 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kFunction:
3345 result = ConvertWord32ToJSBool(
3346 __ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable,
3347 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone));
3348 break;
3349 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kBoolean:
3350 result = __ Select(__ RootEqual(input, RootIndex::kTrueValue, isolate_),
3351 __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value()),
3352 ConvertWord32ToJSBool(__ RootEqual(
3353 input, RootIndex::kFalseValue, isolate_)),
3354 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
3355 SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
3356 break;
3357 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kUndefined:
3358 result = __ Select(__ RootEqual(input, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_),
3359 __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->false_value()),
3360 ConvertWord32ToJSBool(__ ObjectIs(
3361 input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kUndetectable,
3362 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone)),
3363 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
3364 SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
3365 break;
3366 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kObject:
3367 result = __ Select(__ ObjectIs(input, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kNonCallable,
3368 ObjectIsOp::InputAssumptions::kNone),
3369 __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value()),
3370 ConvertWord32ToJSBool(__ RootEqual(
3371 input, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_)),
3372 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
3373 SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
3374 break;
3375 case interpreter::TestTypeOfFlags::LiteralFlag::kOther:
3376 UNREACHABLE(); // Should never be emitted.
3377 }
3378
3379 SetMap(node, result);
3380 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3381 }

3399 __ ObjectIs(receiver, ObjectIsOp::Kind::kDetectableCallable,
3400 assumptions),
3401 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotDetectableReceiver,
3402 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());

3404 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

3510
3511 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Switch* node,
3512 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3513 if (is_visiting_generator_main_switch_) {
3514 // This is the main resume-switch for a generator, and some of its target
3515 // bypass loop headers. We need to re-route the destinations to the
3516 // bypassed loop headers, where secondary switches will be inserted.
3517
3518 compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
3519 __ output_graph().graph_zone()
3520 -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
3521 node->size());
3522
3523 DCHECK_EQ(0, node->value_base());
3524
3525 for (int i = 0; i < node->size(); i++) {
3526 maglev::BasicBlock* target = node->targets()[i].block_ptr();
3527 if (generator_analyzer_.JumpBypassesHeader(target)) {
3528 Block* new_dst = __ NewBlock();
3529
3530 const maglev::BasicBlock* innermost_bypassed_header =
3531 generator_analyzer_.GetInnermostBypassedHeader(target);
3532
3533 pre_loop_generator_blocks_[innermost_bypassed_header].push_back(
3534 {new_dst, Map(target), i});
3535
3536 // {innermost_bypassed_header} is only the innermost bypassed header.
3537 // We also need to record bypasses of outer headers. In the end, we
3538 // want this main Switch to go to before the outermost header, which
3539 // will dispatch to the next inner loop, and so on until the innermost
3540 // loop header and then to the initial destination.
3541 for (const maglev::BasicBlock* bypassed_header =
3542 generator_analyzer_.GetLoopHeader(innermost_bypassed_header);
3543 bypassed_header != nullptr;
3544 bypassed_header =
3545 generator_analyzer_.GetLoopHeader(bypassed_header)) {
3546 Block* prev_loop_dst = __ NewBlock();
3547 pre_loop_generator_blocks_[bypassed_header].push_back(
3548 {prev_loop_dst, new_dst, i});
3549 new_dst = prev_loop_dst;
3550 }
3551
3552 cases[i] = {i, new_dst, BranchHint::kNone};
3553
3554 } else {
3555 cases[i] = {i, Map(target), BranchHint::kNone};
3556 }
3557 }
3558
3559 Block* default_block = __ NewBlock();
3560 __ Switch(Map(node->value()), base::VectorOf(cases, node->size()),
3561 default_block);
3562 __ Bind(default_block);
3563 __ Unreachable();
3564
3565 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3566 }
3567
3568 compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case* cases =
3569 __ output_graph().graph_zone()
3570 -> AllocateArray<compiler::turboshaft::SwitchOp::Case>(
3571 node->size());
3572 int case_value_base = node->value_base();
3573 for (int i = 0; i < node->size(); i++) {
3574 cases[i] = {i + case_value_base, Map(node->targets()[i].block_ptr()),
3575 BranchHint::kNone};
3576 }
3577 Block* default_block;
3578 bool emit_default_block = false;
3579 if (node->has_fallthrough()) {
3580 default_block = Map(state.next_block());
3581 } else {
3582 default_block = __ NewBlock();
3583 emit_default_block = true;
3584 }
3585 __ Switch(Map(node->value()), base::VectorOf(cases, node->size()),
3586 default_block);
3587 if (emit_default_block) {
3588 __ Bind(default_block);
3589 __ Unreachable();
3590 }
3591 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3592 }

3739#define PROCESS_INT32_SHIFT(MaglevName, TurboshaftName) \
3740 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32##MaglevName* node, \
3741 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) { \
3742 V<Word32> right = Map(node->right_input()); \
3743 if (!SupportedOperations::word32_shift_is_safe()) { \
3744 /* JavaScript spec says that the right-hand side of a shift should be \
3745 * taken modulo 32. Some architectures do this automatically, some \
3746 * don't. For those that don't, which do this modulo 32 with a `& 0x1f`. \
3747 */ \
3748 right = __ Word32BitwiseAnd(right, 0x1f); \

3751 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue; \
3752 }

3779 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32AbsWithOverflow* node,
3780 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3781 V<Word32> input = Map(node->input());
3782 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
3783 ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this, input);
3784
3785 IF (__ Int32LessThan(input, 0)) {
3786 V<Tuple<Word32, Word32>> result_with_ovf =
3787 __ Int32MulCheckOverflow(input, -1);
3788 __ DeoptimizeIf(__ Projection<1>(result_with_ovf), frame_state,
3789 DeoptimizeReason::kOverflow,
3790 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
3791 result = __ Projection<0>(result_with_ovf);
3792 }
3793
3794 SetMap(node, result);
3795 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3796 }

3808 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Float64Round* node,
3809 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3810 if (node->kind() == maglev::Float64Round::Kind::kFloor) {
3811 SetMap(node, __ Float64RoundDown(Map(node->input())));
3812 } else if (node->kind() == maglev::Float64Round::Kind::kCeil) {
3813 SetMap(node, __ Float64RoundUp(Map(node->input())));
3814 } else {
3815 DCHECK_EQ(node->kind(), maglev::Float64Round::Kind::kNearest);
3816 // Nearest rounds to +infinity on ties. We emulate this by rounding up and
3817 // adjusting if the difference exceeds 0.5 (like SimplifiedLowering does
3818 // for lower Float64Round).
3819 OpIndex input = Map(node->input());
3820 ScopedVar<Float64, AssemblerT> result(this, __ Float64RoundUp(input));
3821 IF_NOT (__ Float64LessThanOrEqual(__ Float64Sub(result, 0.5), input)) {
3822 result = __ Float64Sub(result, 1.0);
3823 }
3824
3825 SetMap(node, result);
3826 }
3827 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3828 }

3833 switch (node->ieee_function()) {
3834#define CASE(MathName, ExpName, EnumName) \
3835 case maglev::Float64Ieee754Unary::Ieee754Function::k##EnumName: \
3836 kind = FloatUnaryOp::Kind::k##EnumName; \
3837 break;
3838 IEEE_754_UNARY_LIST(CASE)
3839#undef CASE
3840 }
3841 SetMap(node, __ Float64Unary(Map(node->input()), kind));
3842 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3843 }

3845 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedSmiIncrement* node,
3846 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3847 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
3848 V<Smi> result;
3849 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
3850 result = __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ Word32SignedAddDeoptOnOverflow(
3851 __ BitcastSmiToWord32(Map(node->value_input())),
3852 Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
3853 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
3854 } else {
3855 // Remember that 32-bit Smis are stored in the upper 32 bits of 64-bit
3856 // qwords. We thus perform a 64-bit addition rather than a 32-bit one,
3857 // despite Smis being only 32 bits.
3858 result = __ BitcastWordPtrToSmi(__ WordPtrSignedAddDeoptOnOverflow(
3859 __ BitcastSmiToWordPtr(Map(node->value_input())),
3860 Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
3861 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
3862 }
3863 SetMap(node, result);
3864 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3865 }
3866 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedSmiDecrement* node,
3867 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
3868 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
3869 V<Smi> result;
3870 if constexpr (SmiValuesAre31Bits()) {
3871 result = __ BitcastWord32ToSmi(__ Word32SignedSubDeoptOnOverflow(
3872 __ BitcastSmiToWord32(Map(node->value_input())),
3873 Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
3874 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
3875 } else {
3876 result = __ BitcastWordPtrToSmi(__ WordPtrSignedSubDeoptOnOverflow(
3877 __ BitcastSmiToWordPtr(Map(node->value_input())),
3878 Smi::FromInt(1).ptr(), frame_state,
3879 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
3880 }
3881 SetMap(node, result);
3882 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
3883 }
3884
3885// Note that Maglev collects feedback in the generic binops and unops, so that
3886// Turbofan has chance to get better feedback. However, once we reach Turbofan,
3887// we stop collecting feedback, since we've tried multiple times to keep
3888// collecting feedback in Turbofan, but it never seemed worth it. The latest
3889// occurence of this was ended by this CL: https://crrev.com/c/4110858.

3897 frame_state, native_context(), \
3898 ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(node))); \

3900 }

4013 template <typename NumberToFloat64Op>
4014 requires(std::is_same_v<NumberToFloat64Op,
4015 maglev::CheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64> ||
4016 std::is_same_v<NumberToFloat64Op,
4017 maglev::CheckedNumberOrOddballToHoleyFloat64>)
4018 maglev::ProcessResult Process(NumberToFloat64Op* node,
4019 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4020 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4021 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind;
4022 switch (node->conversion_type()) {
4023 case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber:
4024 kind = ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber;
4025 break;
4026 case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean:
4027 kind = ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
4028 kNumberOrBoolean;
4029 break;
4030 case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball:
4031 kind = ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
4032 kNumberOrOddball;
4033 break;
4034 }
4035 SetMap(node,
4036 __ ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt(
4037 Map(node->input()), frame_state, kind,
4038 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kFloat64,
4039 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero,
4040 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4041 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4042 }
4043 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::UncheckedNumberOrOddballToFloat64* node,
4044 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4045 // `node->conversion_type()` doesn't matter here, since for both HeapNumbers
4046 // and Oddballs, the Float64 value is at the same index (and this node never
4047 // deopts, regardless of its input).
4048 SetMap(node, __ ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntagged(
4049 Map(node->input()),
4050 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kFloat64,
4051 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::
4052 kNumberOrOddball));
4053 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4054 }

4084 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedObjectToIndex* node,
4085 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4086 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4087 const FeedbackSource& feedback =
4088 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update();
4089 OpIndex result = __ ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt(
4090 Map(node->object_input()), frame_state,
4091 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumberOrString,
4092 ConvertJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kArrayIndex,
4093 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero, feedback);
4094 if constexpr (Is64()) {
4095 // ArrayIndex is 32-bit in Maglev, but 64 in Turboshaft. This means that
4096 // we have to convert it to 32-bit before the following `SetMap`, and we
4097 // thus have to check that it actually fits in a Uint32.
4098 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(__ Uint64LessThanOrEqual(
4099 result, std::numeric_limits<uint32_t>::max()),
4100 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotInt32, feedback);
4101 RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE();
4102 }
4103 SetMap(node, Is64() ? __ TruncateWord64ToWord32(result) : result);
4104 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4105 }

4134 maglev::ProcessResult Process(
4135 maglev::CheckedTruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32* node,
4136 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4137 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::InputRequirement input_requirement;
4138 switch (node->conversion_type()) {
4139 case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kOnlyNumber:
4140 input_requirement =
4141 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::InputRequirement::kNumber;
4142 break;
4143 case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrBoolean:
4144 input_requirement = TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::
4145 InputRequirement::kNumberOrBoolean;
4146 break;
4147 case maglev::TaggedToFloat64ConversionType::kNumberOrOddball:
4148 input_requirement = TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::
4149 InputRequirement::kNumberOrOddball;
4150 break;
4151 }
4152 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4153 SetMap(
4154 node,
4155 __ TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeopt(
4156 Map(node->input()), frame_state,
4157 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOrDeoptOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32,
4158 input_requirement, node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update()));
4159 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4160 }
4161 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::TruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32* node,
4162 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4163 // In Maglev, TruncateNumberOrOddballToInt32 does the same thing for both
4164 // NumberOrOddball and Number; except when debug_code is enabled: then,
4165 // Maglev inserts runtime checks ensuring that the input is indeed a Number
4166 // or NumberOrOddball. Turboshaft doesn't typically introduce such runtime
4167 // checks, so we instead just lower both Number and NumberOrOddball to the
4168 // NumberOrOddball variant.
4169 SetMap(node, __ TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged(
4170 Map(node->input()),
4171 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kInt32,
4172 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions::
4173 kNumberOrOddball));
4174 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4175 }

4198 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ConvertHoleToUndefined* node,
4199 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4200 V<Word32> cond = RootEqual(node->object_input(), RootIndex::kTheHoleValue);
4201 SetMap(node,
4202 __ Select(cond, __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->undefined_value()),
4203 Map<Object>(node->object_input()),
4204 RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(), BranchHint::kNone,
4205 SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch));
4206 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;

4208 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::ConvertReceiver* node,
4209 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4210 NoThrowingScopeRequired no_throws(node);
4211
4212 Label<Object> done(this);
4213 Label<> non_js_receiver(this);
4214 V<Object> receiver = Map(node->receiver_input());
4215
4216 GOTO_IF(__ IsSmi(receiver), non_js_receiver);
4217
4218 GOTO_IF(__ JSAnyIsNotPrimitive(V<HeapObject>::Cast(receiver)), done,
4219 receiver);
4220
4221 if (node->mode() != ConvertReceiverMode::kNotNullOrUndefined) {
4222 Label<> convert_global_proxy(this);
4223 GOTO_IF(__ RootEqual(receiver, RootIndex::kUndefinedValue, isolate_),
4224 convert_global_proxy);
4225 GOTO_IF_NOT(__ RootEqual(receiver, RootIndex::kNullValue, isolate_),
4226 non_js_receiver);
4227 GOTO(convert_global_proxy);
4228 BIND(convert_global_proxy);
4229 GOTO(done,
4230 __ HeapConstant(
4231 node->native_context().global_proxy_object(broker_).object()));
4232 } else {
4233 GOTO(non_js_receiver);
4234 }
4235
4236 BIND(non_js_receiver);
4237 GOTO(done, __ CallBuiltin_ToObject(
4238 isolate_, __ HeapConstant(node->native_context().object()),
4239 V<JSPrimitive>::Cast(receiver)));
4240
4241 BIND(done, result);
4242 SetMap(node, result);
4243
4244 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4245 }
4246
4247 static constexpr int kMinClampedUint8 = 0;
4248 static constexpr int kMaxClampedUint8 = 255;
4249 V<Word32> Int32ToUint8Clamped(V<Word32> value) {
4250 ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4251 IF (__ Int32LessThan(value, kMinClampedUint8)) {
4252 result = __ Word32Constant(kMinClampedUint8);
4253 } ELSE IF (__ Int32LessThan(value, kMaxClampedUint8)) {
4254 result = value;
4255 } ELSE {
4256 result = __ Word32Constant(kMaxClampedUint8);
4257 }
4258 return result;
4259 }
4260 V<Word32> Float64ToUint8Clamped(V<Float64> value) {
4261 ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4262 IF (__ Float64LessThan(value, kMinClampedUint8)) {
4263 result = __ Word32Constant(kMinClampedUint8);
4264 } ELSE IF (__ Float64LessThan(kMaxClampedUint8, value)) {
4265 result = __ Word32Constant(kMaxClampedUint8);
4266 } ELSE {
4267 // Note that this case handles values that are in range of Clamped Uint8
4268 // and NaN. The order of the IF/ELSE-IF/ELSE in this function is so that
4269 // we do indeed end up here for NaN.
4270 result = __ JSTruncateFloat64ToWord32(__ Float64RoundTiesEven(value));
4271 }
4272 return result;
4273 }
4274
4275 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Int32ToUint8Clamped* node,
4276 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4277 SetMap(node, Int32ToUint8Clamped(Map(node->input())));
4278 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4279 }
4280 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Uint32ToUint8Clamped* node,
4281 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4282 ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4283 V<Word32> value = Map(node->input());
4284 IF (__ Uint32LessThan(value, kMaxClampedUint8)) {
4285 result = value;
4286 } ELSE {
4287 result = __ Word32Constant(kMaxClampedUint8);
4288 }
4289 SetMap(node, result);
4290 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4291 }
4292 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::Float64ToUint8Clamped* node,
4293 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4294 SetMap(node, Float64ToUint8Clamped(Map(node->input())));
4295 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4296 }
4297 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::CheckedNumberToUint8Clamped* node,
4298 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4299 ScopedVar<Word32, AssemblerT> result(this);
4300 V<Object> value = Map(node->input());
4301 GET_FRAME_STATE_MAYBE_ABORT(frame_state, node->eager_deopt_info());
4302 IF (__ IsSmi(value)) {
4303 result = Int32ToUint8Clamped(__ UntagSmi(V<Smi>::Cast(value)));
4304 } ELSE {
4305 V<i::Map> map = __ LoadMapField(value);
4306 __ DeoptimizeIfNot(
4307 __ TaggedEqual(map,
4308 __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->heap_number_map())),
4309 frame_state, DeoptimizeReason::kNotAHeapNumber,
4310 node->eager_deopt_info()->feedback_to_update());
4311 result = Float64ToUint8Clamped(
4312 __ LoadHeapNumberValue(V<HeapNumber>::Cast(value)));
4313 }
4314 RETURN_IF_UNREACHABLE();
4315 SetMap(node, result);
4316 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4317 }

4354 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::GeneratorStore* node,
4355 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4356 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 32> parameters_and_registers;
4357 int num_parameters_and_registers = node->num_parameters_and_registers();
4358 for (int i = 0; i < num_parameters_and_registers; i++) {
4359 parameters_and_registers.push_back(
4360 Map(node->parameters_and_registers(i)));
4361 }
4362 __ GeneratorStore(Map(node->context_input()), Map(node->generator_input()),
4363 parameters_and_registers, node->suspend_id(),
4364 node->bytecode_offset());
4365 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4366 }
4367 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::GeneratorRestoreRegister* node,
4368 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
4369 V<FixedArray> array = Map(node->array_input());
4370 V<Object> result =
4371 __ LoadTaggedField(array, FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(node->index()));
4372 __ Store(array, Map(node->stale_input()), StoreOp::Kind::TaggedBase(),
4373 MemoryRepresentation::TaggedSigned(),
4374 WriteBarrierKind::kNoWriteBarrier,
4375 FixedArray::OffsetOfElementAt(node->index()));
4376
4377 SetMap(node, result);
4378
4379 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4380 }

4480
4481 maglev::ProcessResult Process(maglev::AssertInt32* node,
4482 const maglev::ProcessingState&) {
4483 bool negate_result = false;
4484 V<Word32> cmp = ConvertInt32Compare(node->left_input(), node->right_input(),
4485 node->condition(), &negate_result);
4486 Label<> abort(this);
4487 Label<> end(this);
4488 if (negate_result) {
4489 GOTO_IF(cmp, abort);
4490 } else {
4491 GOTO_IF_NOT(cmp, abort);
4492 }
4493 GOTO(end);
4494
4495 BIND(abort);
4496 __ RuntimeAbort(node->reason());
4497 __ Unreachable();
4498
4499 BIND(end);
4500 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
4501 }

4509 }

4544 private:
4545 OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4546 maglev::EagerDeoptInfo* eager_deopt_info) {
4547 deduplicator_.Reset();
4548 // Eager deopts don't have a result location/size.
4549 const interpreter::Register result_location =
4550 interpreter::Register::invalid_value();
4551 const int result_size = 0;
4552 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects =
4553 maglev::GetVirtualObjects(eager_deopt_info->top_frame());
4554
4555 switch (eager_deopt_info->top_frame().type()) {
4556 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
4557 return BuildFrameState(eager_deopt_info->top_frame().as_interpreted(),
4558 virtual_objects, result_location, result_size);
4559 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
4560 return BuildFrameState(
4561 eager_deopt_info->top_frame().as_builtin_continuation(),
4562 virtual_objects);
4563 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
4564 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
4565 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4566 }
4567 }
4568
4569 OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4570 maglev::LazyDeoptInfo* lazy_deopt_info) {
4571 deduplicator_.Reset();
4572 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects =
4573 maglev::GetVirtualObjects(lazy_deopt_info->top_frame());
4574 switch (lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().type()) {
4575 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
4576 return BuildFrameState(
4577 lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().as_interpreted(), virtual_objects,
4578 lazy_deopt_info->result_location(), lazy_deopt_info->result_size());
4579 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
4580 return BuildFrameState(lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().as_construct_stub(),
4581 virtual_objects);
4582
4583 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
4584 return BuildFrameState(
4585 lazy_deopt_info->top_frame().as_builtin_continuation(),
4586 virtual_objects);
4587
4588 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
4589 UNIMPLEMENTED();
4590 }
4591 }
4592
4593 OptionalV<FrameState> BuildParentFrameState(
4594 maglev::DeoptFrame& frame,
4595 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects) {
4596 // Only the topmost frame should have a valid result_location and
4597 // result_size. One reason for this is that, in Maglev, the PokeAt is not an
4598 // attribute of the DeoptFrame but rather of the LazyDeoptInfo (to which the
4599 // topmost frame is attached).
4600 const interpreter::Register result_location =
4601 interpreter::Register::invalid_value();
4602 const int result_size = 0;
4603
4604 switch (frame.type()) {
4605 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInterpretedFrame:
4606 return BuildFrameState(frame.as_interpreted(), virtual_objects,
4607 result_location, result_size);
4608 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kConstructInvokeStubFrame:
4609 return BuildFrameState(frame.as_construct_stub(), virtual_objects);
4610 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kInlinedArgumentsFrame:
4611 return BuildFrameState(frame.as_inlined_arguments(), virtual_objects);
4612 case maglev::DeoptFrame::FrameType::kBuiltinContinuationFrame:
4613 return BuildFrameState(frame.as_builtin_continuation(),
4614 virtual_objects);
4615 }
4616 }
4617
4618 OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4619 maglev::ConstructInvokeStubDeoptFrame& frame,
4620 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects) {
4621 FrameStateData::Builder builder;
4622 if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
4623 OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
4624 BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
4625 if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4626 builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
4627 }
4628
4629 // Closure
4630 // TODO(dmercadier): ConstructInvokeStub frames don't have a Closure input,
4631 // but the instruction selector assumes that they do and that it should be
4632 // skipped. We thus use SmiConstant(0) as a fake Closure input here, but it
4633 // would be nicer to fix the instruction selector to not require this input
4634 // at all for such frames.
4635 V<Any> fake_closure_input = __ SmiZeroConstant();
4636 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(), fake_closure_input);
4637
4638 // Parameters
4639 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.receiver());
4640
4641 // Context
4642 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.context());
4643
4644 if (builder.Inputs().size() >
4645 std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
4646 *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
4647 return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4648 }
4649
4650 const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame);
4651 return __ FrameState(
4652 builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
4653 builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
4654 }
4655
4656 OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4657 maglev::InlinedArgumentsDeoptFrame& frame,
4658 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects) {
4659 FrameStateData::Builder builder;
4660 if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
4661 OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
4662 BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
4663 if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4664 builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
4665 }
4666
4667 // Closure
4668 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.closure());
4669
4670 // Parameters
4671 for (const maglev::ValueNode* arg : frame.arguments()) {
4672 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, arg);
4673 }
4674
4675 // Context
4676 // TODO(dmercadier): InlinedExtraArguments frames don't have a Context
4677 // input, but the instruction selector assumes that they do and that it
4678 // should be skipped. We thus use SmiConstant(0) as a fake Context input
4679 // here, but it would be nicer to fix the instruction selector to not
4680 // require this input at all for such frames.
4681 V<Any> fake_context_input = __ SmiZeroConstant();
4682 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(), fake_context_input);
4683
4684 if (builder.Inputs().size() >
4685 std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
4686 *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
4687 return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4688 }
4689
4690 const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame);
4691 return __ FrameState(
4692 builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
4693 builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
4694 }
4695
4696 OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4697 maglev::BuiltinContinuationDeoptFrame& frame,
4698 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects) {
4699 FrameStateData::Builder builder;
4700 if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
4701 OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
4702 BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
4703 if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4704 builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
4705 }
4706
4707 // Closure
4708 if (frame.is_javascript()) {
4709 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4710 __ HeapConstant(frame.javascript_target().object()));
4711 } else {
4712 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
4713 }
4714
4715 // Parameters
4716 for (maglev::ValueNode* param : frame.parameters()) {
4717 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, param);
4718 }
4719
4720 // Extra fixed JS frame parameters. These are at the end since JS builtins
4721 // push their parameters in reverse order.
4722 constexpr int kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters =
4723 V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL ? 4 : 3;
4724 if (frame.is_javascript()) {
4725 DCHECK_EQ(Builtins::CallInterfaceDescriptorFor(frame.builtin_id())
4726 .GetRegisterParameterCount(),
4727 kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters);
4728 static_assert(kExtraFixedJSFrameParameters ==
4729 3 + (V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE_BOOL ? 1 : 0));
4730 // kJavaScriptCallTargetRegister
4731 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4732 __ HeapConstant(frame.javascript_target().object()));
4733 // kJavaScriptCallNewTargetRegister
4734 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4735 __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->undefined_value()));
4736 // kJavaScriptCallArgCountRegister
4737 builder.AddInput(
4738 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4739 __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(
4740 Builtins::GetStackParameterCount(frame.builtin_id()))));
4741#ifdef V8_JS_LINKAGE_INCLUDES_DISPATCH_HANDLE
4742 // kJavaScriptCallDispatchHandleRegister
4743 builder.AddInput(
4744 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4745 __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(kInvalidDispatchHandle.value())));
4746#endif
4747 }
4748
4749 // Context
4750 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.context());
4751
4752 if (builder.Inputs().size() >
4753 std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
4754 *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
4755 return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4756 }
4757
4758 const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame);
4759 return __ FrameState(
4760 builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
4761 builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
4762 }
4763
4764 OptionalV<FrameState> BuildFrameState(
4765 maglev::InterpretedDeoptFrame& frame,
4766 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects,
4767 interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) {
4768 DCHECK_EQ(result_size != 0, result_location.is_valid());
4769 FrameStateData::Builder builder;
4770
4771 if (frame.parent() != nullptr) {
4772 OptionalV<FrameState> parent_frame =
4773 BuildParentFrameState(*frame.parent(), virtual_objects);
4774 if (!parent_frame.has_value()) return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4775 builder.AddParentFrameState(parent_frame.value());
4776 }
4777
4778 // Closure
4779 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, frame.closure());
4780
4781 // Parameters
4782 frame.frame_state()->ForEachParameter(
4783 frame.unit(), [&](maglev::ValueNode* value, interpreter::Register reg) {
4784 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, value, reg, result_location,
4785 result_size);
4786 });
4787
4788 // Context
4789 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects,
4790 frame.frame_state()->context(frame.unit()));
4791
4792 // Locals
4793 // ForEachLocal in Maglev skips over dead registers, but we still need to
4794 // call AddUnusedRegister on the Turboshaft FrameStateData Builder.
4795 // {local_index} is used to keep track of such unused registers.
4796 // Among the variables not included in ForEachLocal is the Accumulator (but
4797 // this is fine since there is an entry in the state specifically for the
4798 // accumulator later).
4799 int local_index = 0;
4800 frame.frame_state()->ForEachLocal(
4801 frame.unit(), [&](maglev::ValueNode* value, interpreter::Register reg) {
4802 while (local_index < reg.index()) {
4803 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
4804 local_index++;
4805 }
4806 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, value, reg, result_location,
4807 result_size);
4808 local_index++;
4809 });
4810 for (; local_index < frame.unit().register_count(); local_index++) {
4811 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
4812 }
4813
4814 // Accumulator
4815 if (frame.frame_state()->liveness()->AccumulatorIsLive()) {
4816 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects,
4817 frame.frame_state()->accumulator(frame.unit()),
4818 interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator(),
4819 result_location, result_size);
4820 } else {
4821 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
4822 }
4823
4824 OutputFrameStateCombine combine =
4825 ComputeCombine(frame, result_location, result_size);
4826
4827 if (builder.Inputs().size() >
4828 std::numeric_limits<decltype(Operation::input_count)>::max() - 1) {
4829 *bailout_ = BailoutReason::kTooManyArguments;
4830 return OptionalV<FrameState>::Nullopt();
4831 }
4832
4833 const FrameStateInfo* frame_state_info = MakeFrameStateInfo(frame, combine);
4834 return __ FrameState(
4835 builder.Inputs(), builder.inlined(),
4836 builder.AllocateFrameStateData(*frame_state_info, graph_zone()));
4837 }
4838
4839 void AddDeoptInput(FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
4840 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects,
4841 const maglev::ValueNode* node) {
4842 if (const maglev::InlinedAllocation* alloc =
4843 node->TryCast<maglev::InlinedAllocation>()) {
4844 DCHECK(alloc->HasBeenAnalysed());
4845 if (alloc->HasBeenElided()) {
4846 AddVirtualObjectInput(builder, virtual_objects,
4847 virtual_objects.FindAllocatedWith(alloc));
4848 return;
4849 }
4850 }
4851 if (const maglev::Identity* ident_obj = node->TryCast<maglev::Identity>()) {
4852 // The value_representation of Identity nodes is always Tagged rather than
4853 // the actual value_representation of their input. We thus bypass identity
4854 // nodes manually here to get to correct value_representation and thus the
4855 // correct MachineType.
4856 node = ident_obj->input(0).node();
4857 // Identity nodes should not have Identity as input.
4858 DCHECK(!node->Is<maglev::Identity>());
4859 }
4860 builder.AddInput(MachineTypeFor(node->value_representation()), Map(node));
4861 }
4862
4863 void AddDeoptInput(FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
4864 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects,
4865 const maglev::ValueNode* node, interpreter::Register reg,
4866 interpreter::Register result_location, int result_size) {
4867 if (result_location.is_valid() && maglev::LazyDeoptInfo::InReturnValues(
4868 reg, result_location, result_size)) {
4869 builder.AddUnusedRegister();
4870 } else {
4871 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, node);
4872 }
4873 }
4874
4875 void AddVirtualObjectInput(FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
4876 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects,
4877 const maglev::VirtualObject* vobj) {
4878 if (vobj->type() == maglev::VirtualObject::kHeapNumber) {
4879 // We need to add HeapNumbers as dematerialized HeapNumbers (rather than
4880 // simply NumberConstant), because they could be mutable HeapNumber
4881 // fields, in which case we don't want GVN to merge them.
4882 constexpr int kNumberOfField = 2; // map + value
4883 builder.AddDematerializedObject(deduplicator_.CreateFreshId().id,
4884 kNumberOfField);
4885 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4886 __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->heap_number_map()));
4887 builder.AddInput(MachineType::Float64(),
4888 __ Float64Constant(vobj->number()));
4889 return;
4890 }
4891
4892 Deduplicator::DuplicatedId dup_id = deduplicator_.GetDuplicatedId(vobj);
4893 if (dup_id.duplicated) {
4894 builder.AddDematerializedObjectReference(dup_id.id);
4895 return;
4896 }
4897 if (vobj->type() == maglev::VirtualObject::kFixedDoubleArray) {
4898 constexpr int kMapAndLengthFieldCount = 2;
4899 uint32_t length = vobj->double_elements_length();
4900 uint32_t field_count = length + kMapAndLengthFieldCount;
4901 builder.AddDematerializedObject(dup_id.id, field_count);
4902 builder.AddInput(
4903 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4904 __ HeapConstantNoHole(local_factory_->fixed_double_array_map()));
4905 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4906 __ SmiConstant(Smi::FromInt(length)));
4907 FixedDoubleArrayRef elements = vobj->double_elements();
4908 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < length; i++) {
4909 i::Float64 value = elements.GetFromImmutableFixedDoubleArray(i);
4910 if (value.is_hole_nan()) {
4911 builder.AddInput(
4912 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4913 __ HeapConstantHole(local_factory_->the_hole_value()));
4914 } else {
4915 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4916 __ NumberConstant(value.get_scalar()));
4917 }
4918 }
4919 return;
4920 }
4921
4922 DCHECK_EQ(vobj->type(), maglev::VirtualObject::kDefault);
4923 constexpr int kMapFieldCount = 1;
4924 uint32_t field_count = vobj->slot_count() + kMapFieldCount;
4925 builder.AddDematerializedObject(dup_id.id, field_count);
4926 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4927 __ HeapConstantNoHole(vobj->map().object()));
4928 for (uint32_t i = 0; i < vobj->slot_count(); i++) {
4929 AddVirtualObjectNestedValue(builder, virtual_objects,
4930 vobj->get_by_index(i));
4931 }
4932 }
4933
4934 void AddVirtualObjectNestedValue(
4935 FrameStateData::Builder& builder,
4936 const maglev::VirtualObject::List& virtual_objects,
4937 const maglev::ValueNode* value) {
4938 if (maglev::IsConstantNode(value->opcode())) {
4939 switch (value->opcode()) {
4940 case maglev::Opcode::kConstant:
4941 builder.AddInput(
4942 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4943 __ HeapConstant(value->Cast<maglev::Constant>()->ref().object()));
4944 break;
4945
4946 case maglev::Opcode::kFloat64Constant:
4947 builder.AddInput(
4948 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4949 __ NumberConstant(value->Cast<maglev::Float64Constant>()
4950 ->value()
4951 .get_scalar()));
4952 break;
4953
4954 case maglev::Opcode::kInt32Constant:
4955 builder.AddInput(
4956 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4957 __ NumberConstant(value->Cast<maglev::Int32Constant>()->value()));
4958 break;
4959
4960 case maglev::Opcode::kUint32Constant:
4961 builder.AddInput(MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4962 __ NumberConstant(
4963 value->Cast<maglev::Uint32Constant>()->value()));
4964 break;
4965
4966 case maglev::Opcode::kRootConstant:
4967 builder.AddInput(
4968 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4969 (__ HeapConstant(Cast<HeapObject>(isolate_->root_handle(
4970 value->Cast<maglev::RootConstant>()->index())))));
4971 break;
4972
4973 case maglev::Opcode::kSmiConstant:
4974 builder.AddInput(
4975 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4976 __ SmiConstant(value->Cast<maglev::SmiConstant>()->value()));
4977 break;
4978
4979 case maglev::Opcode::kTrustedConstant:
4980 builder.AddInput(
4981 MachineType::AnyTagged(),
4982 __ TrustedHeapConstant(
4983 value->Cast<maglev::TrustedConstant>()->object().object()));
4984 break;
4985
4986 case maglev::Opcode::kTaggedIndexConstant:
4987 case maglev::Opcode::kExternalConstant:
4988 default:
4989 UNREACHABLE();
4990 }
4991 return;
4992 }
4993
4994 // Special nodes.
4995 switch (value->opcode()) {
4996 case maglev::Opcode::kArgumentsElements:
4997 builder.AddArgumentsElements(
4998 value->Cast<maglev::ArgumentsElements>()->type());
4999 break;
5000 case maglev::Opcode::kArgumentsLength:
5001 builder.AddArgumentsLength();
5002 break;
5003 case maglev::Opcode::kRestLength:
5004 builder.AddRestLength();
5005 break;
5006 case maglev::Opcode::kVirtualObject:
5007 UNREACHABLE();
5008 default:
5009 AddDeoptInput(builder, virtual_objects, value);
5010 break;
5011 }
5012 }
5013
5014 class Deduplicator {
5015 public:
5016 struct DuplicatedId {
5017 uint32_t id;
5018 bool duplicated;
5019 };
5020 DuplicatedId GetDuplicatedId(const maglev::VirtualObject* object) {
5021 // TODO(dmercadier): do better than a linear search here.
5022 for (uint32_t idx = 0; idx < object_ids_.size(); idx++) {
5023 if (object_ids_[idx] == object) {
5024 return {idx, true};
5025 }
5026 }
5027 object_ids_.push_back(object);
5028 return {next_id_++, false};
5029 }
5030
5031 DuplicatedId CreateFreshId() { return {next_id_++, false}; }
5032
5033 void Reset() {
5034 object_ids_.clear();
5035 next_id_ = 0;
5036 }
5037
5038 static const uint32_t kNotDuplicated = -1;
5039
5040 private:
5041 std::vector<const maglev::VirtualObject*> object_ids_;
5042 uint32_t next_id_ = 0;
5043 };

5154
5155 enum class Sign { kSigned, kUnsigned };
5156 template <typename rep>
5157 V<Word32> ConvertCompare(maglev::Input left_input, maglev::Input right_input,
5158 ::Operation operation, Sign sign) {
5159 DCHECK_IMPLIES(
5160 (std::is_same_v<rep, Float64> || std::is_same_v<rep, Float32>),
5161 sign == Sign::kSigned);
5162 ComparisonOp::Kind kind;
5163 bool swap_inputs = false;
5164 switch (operation) {
5165 case ::Operation::kEqual:
5166 case ::Operation::kStrictEqual:
5167 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
5168 break;
5169 case ::Operation::kLessThan:
5170 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan
5171 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5172 break;
5173 case ::Operation::kLessThanOrEqual:
5174 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned
5175 ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual
5176 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5177 break;
5178 case ::Operation::kGreaterThan:
5179 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan
5180 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5181 swap_inputs = true;
5182 break;
5183 case ::Operation::kGreaterThanOrEqual:
5184 kind = sign == Sign::kSigned
5185 ? ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual
5186 : ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5187 swap_inputs = true;
5188 break;
5189 default:
5190 UNREACHABLE();
5191 }
5192 V<rep> left = Map(left_input);
5193 V<rep> right = Map(right_input);
5194 if (swap_inputs) std::swap(left, right);
5195 return __ Comparison(left, right, kind, V<rep>::rep);
5196 }
5197
5198 V<Word32> ConvertInt32Compare(maglev::Input left_input,
5199 maglev::Input right_input,
5200 maglev::AssertCondition condition,
5201 bool* negate_result) {
5202 ComparisonOp::Kind kind;
5203 bool swap_inputs = false;
5204 switch (condition) {
5205 case maglev::AssertCondition::kEqual:
5206 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
5207 break;
5208 case maglev::AssertCondition::kNotEqual:
5209 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kEqual;
5210 *negate_result = true;
5211 break;
5212 case maglev::AssertCondition::kLessThan:
5213 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan;
5214 break;
5215 case maglev::AssertCondition::kLessThanEqual:
5216 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual;
5217 break;
5218 case maglev::AssertCondition::kGreaterThan:
5219 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThan;
5220 swap_inputs = true;
5221 break;
5222 case maglev::AssertCondition::kGreaterThanEqual:
5223 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kSignedLessThanOrEqual;
5224 swap_inputs = true;
5225 break;
5226 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThan:
5227 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5228 break;
5229 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedLessThanEqual:
5230 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5231 break;
5232 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThan:
5233 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThan;
5234 swap_inputs = true;
5235 break;
5236 case maglev::AssertCondition::kUnsignedGreaterThanEqual:
5237 kind = ComparisonOp::Kind::kUnsignedLessThanOrEqual;
5238 swap_inputs = true;
5239 break;
5240 }
5241 V<Word32> left = Map(left_input);
5242 V<Word32> right = Map(right_input);
5243 if (swap_inputs) std::swap(left, right);
5244 return __ Comparison(left, right, kind, WordRepresentation::Word32());
5245 }

5247 V<Word32> RootEqual(maglev::Input input, RootIndex root) {
5248 return __ RootEqual(Map(input), root, isolate_);
5249 }

5289
5290 V<Number> Float64ToTagged(
5291 V<Float64> input,
5292 maglev::Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode conversion_mode) {
5293 // Float64ToTagged's conversion mode is used to control whether integer
5294 // floats should be converted to Smis or to HeapNumbers: kCanonicalizeSmi
5295 // means that they can be converted to Smis, and otherwise they should
5296 // remain HeapNumbers.
5297 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind kind =
5298 conversion_mode ==
5299 maglev::Float64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi
5300 ? ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kNumber
5301 : ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kHeapNumber;
5302 return V<Number>::Cast(__ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
5303 input, kind, RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
5304 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
5305 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero));
5306 }
5307
5308 V<NumberOrUndefined> HoleyFloat64ToTagged(
5309 V<Float64> input,
5310 maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode conversion_mode) {
5311 Label<NumberOrUndefined> done(this);
5312 if (conversion_mode ==
5313 maglev::HoleyFloat64ToTagged::ConversionMode::kCanonicalizeSmi) {
5314 // ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive cannot at the same time canonicalize smis
5315 // and handle holes. We thus manually insert a smi check when the
5316 // conversion_mode is CanonicalizeSmi.
5317 IF (__ Float64IsSmi(input)) {
5318 V<Word32> as_int32 = __ TruncateFloat64ToInt32OverflowUndefined(input);
5319 V<Smi> as_smi = V<Smi>::Cast(__ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
5320 as_int32, ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::kSmi,
5321 RegisterRepresentation::Word32(),
5322 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
5323 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kDontCheckForMinusZero));
5324 GOTO(done, as_smi);
5325 }
5326 }
5327 V<NumberOrUndefined> as_obj =
5328 V<NumberOrUndefined>::Cast(__ ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitive(
5329 input,
5330 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::JSPrimitiveKind::
5331 kHeapNumberOrUndefined,
5332 RegisterRepresentation::Float64(),
5333 ConvertUntaggedToJSPrimitiveOp::InputInterpretation::kSigned,
5334 CheckForMinusZeroMode::kCheckForMinusZero));
5335 if (done.has_incoming_jump()) {
5336 GOTO(done, as_obj);
5337 BIND(done, result);
5338 return result;
5339 } else {
5340 // Avoid creating a new block if {as_obj} is the only possible return
5341 // value.
5342 return as_obj;
5343 }
5344 }
5345
5346 void FixLoopPhis(maglev::BasicBlock* loop) {
5347 DCHECK(loop->is_loop());
5348 if (!loop->has_phi()) return;
5349 for (maglev::Phi* maglev_phi : *loop->phis()) {
5350 // Note that we've already emited the backedge Goto, which means that
5351 // we're currently not in a block, which means that we need to pass
5352 // can_be_invalid=false to `Map`, otherwise it will think that we're
5353 // currently emitting unreachable operations and return
5354 // OpIndex::Invalid().
5355 constexpr bool kIndexCanBeInvalid = false;
5356 OpIndex phi_index = Map(maglev_phi, kIndexCanBeInvalid);
5357 PendingLoopPhiOp& pending_phi =
5358 __ output_graph().Get(phi_index).Cast<PendingLoopPhiOp>();
5359 __ output_graph().Replace<PhiOp>(
5360 phi_index,
5361 base::VectorOf(
5362 {pending_phi.first(),
5363 Map(maglev_phi -> backedge_input(), kIndexCanBeInvalid)}),
5364 pending_phi.rep);
5365 }
5366 }
5367
5368 RegisterRepresentation RegisterRepresentationFor(
5369 maglev::ValueRepresentation value_rep) {
5370 switch (value_rep) {
5371 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kTagged:
5372 return RegisterRepresentation::Tagged();
5373 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kInt32:
5374 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kUint32:
5375 return RegisterRepresentation::Word32();
5376 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kFloat64:
5377 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kHoleyFloat64:
5378 return RegisterRepresentation::Float64();
5379 case maglev::ValueRepresentation::kIntPtr:
5380 return RegisterRepresentation::WordPtr();
5381 }
5382 }
5383
5384 // TODO(dmercadier): Using a Branch would open more optimization opportunities
5385 // for BranchElimination compared to using a Select. However, in most cases,
5386 // Maglev should avoid materializing JS booleans, so there is a good chance
5387 // that it we actually need to do it, it's because we have to, and
5388 // BranchElimination probably cannot help. Thus, using a Select rather than a
5389 // Branch leads to smaller graphs, which is generally beneficial. Still, once
5390 // the graph builder is finished, we should evaluate whether Select or Branch
5391 // is the best choice here.
5392 V<Boolean> ConvertWord32ToJSBool(V<Word32> b, bool flip = false) {
5393 V<Boolean> true_idx = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->true_value());
5394 V<Boolean> false_idx = __ HeapConstant(local_factory_->false_value());
5395 if (flip) std::swap(true_idx, false_idx);
5396 return __ Select(b, true_idx, false_idx, RegisterRepresentation::Tagged(),
5397 BranchHint::kNone, SelectOp::Implementation::kBranch);
5398 }
5399
5400 // This function corresponds to MaglevAssembler::ToBoolean.
5401 V<Word32> ToBit(
5402 maglev::Input input,
5403 TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::InputAssumptions assumptions) {
5404 // TODO(dmercadier): {input} in Maglev is of type Object (like, any
5405 // HeapObject or Smi). However, the implementation of ToBoolean in Maglev is
5406 // identical to the lowering of TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp(kBit) in
5407 // Turboshaft (which is done in MachineLoweringReducer), so we're using
5408 // TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp with a non-JSPrimitive input (but it
5409 // still works). We should avoid doing this to avoid any confusion. Renaming
5410 // TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged to TruncateObjectToUntagged might be the
5411 // proper fix, in particular because it seems that the Turbofan input to
5412 // this operation is indeed an Object rather than a JSPrimitive (since
5413 // we use this operation in the regular TF->TS graph builder to translate
5414 // TruncateTaggedToBit and TruncateTaggedPointerToBit).
5415 return V<Word32>::Cast(__ TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntagged(
5416 Map(input.node()), TruncateJSPrimitiveToUntaggedOp::UntaggedKind::kBit,
5417 assumptions));
5418 }

5420 // Converts a Float64 to a Word32 boolean, correctly producing 0 for NaN, by
5421 // relying on the fact that "0.0 < abs(x)" is only false for NaN and 0.
5422 V<Word32> Float64ToBit(V<Float64> input) {
5423 return __ Float64LessThan(0.0, __ Float64Abs(input));
5424 }
5425
5426 LazyDeoptOnThrow ShouldLazyDeoptOnThrow(maglev::NodeBase* node) {
5427 if (!node->properties().can_throw()) return LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo;
5428 const maglev::ExceptionHandlerInfo* info = node->exception_handler_info();
5429 if (info->ShouldLazyDeopt()) return LazyDeoptOnThrow::kYes;
5430 return LazyDeoptOnThrow::kNo;
5431 }
5432
5433 class ThrowingScope {
5434 // In Maglev, exception handlers have no predecessors, and their Phis are a
5435 // bit special: they all correspond to interpreter registers, and get
5436 // eventually initialized with the value that their predecessors have for
5437 // the corresponding interpreter registers.
5438
5439 // In Turboshaft, exception handlers have predecessors and contain regular
5440 // phis. Creating a ThrowingScope takes care of recording in Variables
5441 // the current value of interpreter registers (right before emitting a node
5442 // that can throw), and sets the current_catch_block of the Assembler.
5443 // Throwing operations that are emitted while the scope is active will
5444 // automatically be wired to the catch handler. Then, when calling
5445 // Process(Phi) on exception phis (= when processing the catch handler),
5446 // these Phis will be mapped to the Variable corresponding to their owning
5447 // intepreter register.
5448
5449 public:
5450 ThrowingScope(GraphBuildingNodeProcessor* builder,
5451 maglev::NodeBase* throwing_node)
5452 : builder_(*builder) {
5453 DCHECK_EQ(__ current_catch_block(), nullptr);
5454 if (!throwing_node->properties().can_throw()) return;
5455 const maglev::ExceptionHandlerInfo* handler_info =
5456 throwing_node->exception_handler_info();
5457 if (!handler_info->HasExceptionHandler() ||
5458 handler_info->ShouldLazyDeopt()) {
5459 return;
5460 }
5461
5462 catch_block_ = handler_info->catch_block.block_ptr();
5463
5464 __ set_current_catch_block(builder_.Map(catch_block_));
5465
5466 // We now need to prepare recording the inputs for the exception phis of
5467 // the catch handler.
5468
5469 if (!catch_block_->has_phi()) {
5470 // Catch handler doesn't have any Phis, no need to do anything else.
5471 return;
5472 }
5473
5474 const maglev::InterpretedDeoptFrame& interpreted_frame =
5475 throwing_node->lazy_deopt_info()->GetFrameForExceptionHandler(
5476 handler_info);
5477 const maglev::CompactInterpreterFrameState* compact_frame =
5478 interpreted_frame.frame_state();
5479 const maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit& maglev_unit =
5480 interpreted_frame.unit();
5481
5482 builder_.IterCatchHandlerPhis(
5483 catch_block_, [this, compact_frame, maglev_unit](
5484 interpreter::Register owner, Variable var) {
5485 DCHECK_NE(owner, interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator());
5486
5487 const maglev::ValueNode* maglev_value =
5488 compact_frame->GetValueOf(owner, maglev_unit);
5489 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(maglev_value);
5490
5491 if (const maglev::VirtualObject* vobj =
5492 maglev_value->TryCast<maglev::VirtualObject>()) {
5493 maglev_value = vobj->allocation();
5494 }
5495
5496 V<Any> ts_value = builder_.Map(maglev_value);
5497 __ SetVariable(var, ts_value);
5498 builder_.RecordRepresentation(ts_value,
5499 maglev_value->value_representation());
5500 });
5501 }
5502
5503 ~ThrowingScope() {
5504 // Resetting the catch handler. It is always set on a case-by-case basis
5505 // before emitting a throwing node, so there is no need to "reset the
5506 // previous catch handler" or something like that, since there is no
5507 // previous handler (there is a DCHECK in the ThrowingScope constructor
5508 // checking that the current_catch_block is indeed nullptr when the scope
5509 // is created).
5510 __ set_current_catch_block(nullptr);
5511
5512 if (catch_block_ == nullptr) return;
5513 if (!catch_block_->has_phi()) return;
5514
5515 // We clear the Variables that we've set when initializing the scope, in
5516 // order to avoid creating Phis for such Variables. These are really only
5517 // meant to be used when translating the Phis in the catch handler, and
5518 // when the scope is destroyed, we shouldn't be in the Catch handler yet.
5519 builder_.IterCatchHandlerPhis(
5520 catch_block_, [this](interpreter::Register, Variable var) {
5521 __ SetVariable(var, V<Object>::Invalid());
5522 });
5523 }
5524
5525 private:
5526 GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::AssemblerT& Asm() { return builder_.Asm(); }
5527 GraphBuildingNodeProcessor& builder_;
5528 const maglev::BasicBlock* catch_block_ = nullptr;
5529 };
5530
5531 class NoThrowingScopeRequired {
5532 public:
5533 explicit NoThrowingScopeRequired(maglev::NodeBase* node) {
5534 // If this DCHECK fails, then the caller should instead use a
5535 // ThrowingScope. Additionally, all of the calls it contains should
5536 // explicitely pass LazyDeoptOnThrow.
5537 DCHECK(!node->properties().can_throw());
5538 }
5539 };
5540
5541 template <typename Function>
5542 void IterCatchHandlerPhis(const maglev::BasicBlock* catch_block,
5543 Function&& callback) {
5544 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(catch_block);
5545 DCHECK(catch_block->has_phi());
5546 for (auto phi : *catch_block->phis()) {
5547 DCHECK(phi->is_exception_phi());
5548 interpreter::Register owner = phi->owner();
5549 if (owner == interpreter::Register::virtual_accumulator()) {
5550 // The accumulator exception phi corresponds to the exception object
5551 // rather than whatever value the accumulator contained before the
5552 // throwing operation. We don't need to iterate here, since there is
5553 // special handling when processing Phis to use `catch_block_begin_`
5554 // for it instead of a Variable.
5555 continue;
5556 }
5557
5558 auto it = regs_to_vars_.find(owner.index());
5559 Variable var;
5560 if (it == regs_to_vars_.end()) {
5561 // We use a LoopInvariantVariable: if loop phis were needed, then the
5562 // Maglev value would already be a loop Phi, and we wouldn't need
5563 // Turboshaft to automatically insert a loop phi.
5564 var = __ NewLoopInvariantVariable(RegisterRepresentation::Tagged());
5565 regs_to_vars_.insert({owner.index(), var});
5566 } else {
5567 var = it->second;
5568 }
5569
5570 callback(owner, var);
5571 }
5572 }
5573
5574 OpIndex MapPhiInput(const maglev::Input input, int input_index) {
5575 return MapPhiInput(input.node(), input_index);
5576 }
5577 OpIndex MapPhiInput(const maglev::NodeBase* node, int input_index) {
5578 if (V8_UNLIKELY(node == maglev_generator_context_node_)) {
5579 OpIndex generator_context = __ GetVariable(generator_context_);
5580 if (__ current_block()->Contains(generator_context)) {
5581 DCHECK(!__ current_block()->IsLoop());
5582 DCHECK(__ output_graph().Get(generator_context).Is<PhiOp>());
5583 // If {generator_context} is a Phi defined in the current block and it's
5584 // used as input for another Phi, then we need to use it's value from
5585 // the correct predecessor, since a Phi can't be an input to another Phi
5586 // in the same block.
5587 return __ GetPredecessorValue(generator_context_, input_index);
5588 }
5589 return generator_context;
5590 }
5591 return Map(node);
5592 }
5593
5594 template <typename T>
5595 V<T> Map(const maglev::Input input, bool can_be_invalid = true) {
5596 return V<T>::Cast(Map(input.node(), can_be_invalid));
5597 }
5598 OpIndex Map(const maglev::Input input, bool can_be_invalid = true) {
5599 return Map(input.node(), can_be_invalid);
5600 }
5601 OpIndex Map(const maglev::NodeBase* node, bool can_be_invalid = true) {
5602 // If {can_be_invalid} is true (which it should be in most cases) and we're
5603 // currently in unreachable code, then `OpIndex::Invalid` is returned. The
5604 // only case where `can_be_invalid` is false is FixLoopPhis: this is called
5605 // after having emitted the backedge Goto, which means that we are in
5606 // unreachable code, but we know that the mappings should still exist.
5607 if (can_be_invalid && __ generating_unreachable_operations()) {
5608 return OpIndex::Invalid();
5609 }
5610 if (V8_UNLIKELY(node == maglev_generator_context_node_)) {
5611 return __ GetVariable(generator_context_);
5612 }
5613 DCHECK(node_mapping_[node].valid());
5614 return node_mapping_[node];
5615 }
5616 Block* Map(const maglev::BasicBlock* block) { return block_mapping_[block]; }
5617
5618 void SetMap(maglev::NodeBase* node, V<Any> idx) {
5619 if (__ generating_unreachable_operations()) return;
5620 DCHECK(idx.valid());
5621 DCHECK_EQ(__ output_graph().Get(idx).outputs_rep().size(), 1);
5622 node_mapping_[node] = idx;
5623 }
5624
5625 void SetMapMaybeMultiReturn(maglev::NodeBase* node, V<Any> idx) {
5626 const Operation& op = __ output_graph().Get(idx);
5627 if (const TupleOp* tuple = op.TryCast<TupleOp>()) {
5628 // If the call returned multiple values, then in Maglev, {node} is
5629 // used as the 1st returned value, and a GetSecondReturnedValue node is
5630 // used to access the 2nd value. We thus call `SetMap` with the 1st
5631 // projection of the call, and record the 2nd projection in
5632 // {second_return_value_}, which we'll use when translating
5633 // GetSecondReturnedValue.
5634 DCHECK_EQ(tuple->input_count, 2);
5635 SetMap(node, tuple->input(0));
5636 second_return_value_ = tuple->input<Object>(1);
5637 } else {
5638 SetMap(node, idx);
5639 }
5640 }
5641
5642 void RecordRepresentation(OpIndex idx, maglev::ValueRepresentation repr) {
5643 DCHECK_IMPLIES(maglev_representations_.contains(idx),
5644 maglev_representations_[idx] == repr);
5645 maglev_representations_[idx] = repr;
5646 }
5647
5648 V<NativeContext> native_context() {
5649 DCHECK(native_context_.valid());
5650 return native_context_;
5651 }
5652
5653 PipelineData* data_;
5654 Zone* temp_zone_;
5655 Isolate* isolate_ = data_->isolate();
5656 LocalIsolate* local_isolate_ = isolate_->AsLocalIsolate();
5657 JSHeapBroker* broker_ = data_->broker();
5658 LocalFactory* local_factory_ = local_isolate_->factory();
5659 AssemblerT assembler_;
5660 maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* maglev_compilation_unit_;
5661 ZoneUnorderedMap<const maglev::NodeBase*, OpIndex> node_mapping_;
5662 ZoneUnorderedMap<const maglev::BasicBlock*, Block*> block_mapping_;
5663 ZoneUnorderedMap<int, Variable> regs_to_vars_;
5664
5665 // The {deduplicator_} is used when building frame states containing escaped
5666 // objects. It could be a local object in `BuildFrameState`, but it's instead
5667 // defined here to recycle its memory.
5668 Deduplicator deduplicator_;
5669
5670 // In Turboshaft, exception blocks start with a CatchBlockBegin. In Maglev,
5671 // there is no such operation, and the exception is instead populated into the
5672 // accumulator by the throwing code, and is then loaded in Maglev through an
5673 // exception phi. When emitting a Turboshaft exception block, we thus store
5674 // the CatchBlockBegin in {catch_block_begin_}, which we then use when trying
5675 // to map the exception phi corresponding to the accumulator.
5676 V<Object> catch_block_begin_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
5677
5678 // Maglev loops can have multiple forward edges, while Turboshaft should only
5679 // have a single one. When a Maglev loop has multiple forward edges, we create
5680 // an additional Turboshaft block before (which we record in
5681 // {loop_single_edge_predecessors_}), and jumps to the loop will instead go to
5682 // this additional block, which will become the only forward predecessor of
5683 // the loop.
5684 ZoneUnorderedMap<const maglev::BasicBlock*, Block*>
5685 loop_single_edge_predecessors_;
5686 // When we create an additional loop predecessor for loops that have multiple
5687 // forward predecessors, we store the newly created phis in
5688 // {loop_phis_first_input_}, so that we can then use them as the first input
5689 // of the original loop phis. {loop_phis_first_input_index_} is used as an
5690 // index in {loop_phis_first_input_} in VisitPhi so that we know where to find
5691 // the first input for the current loop phi.
5692 base::SmallVector<OpIndex, 16> loop_phis_first_input_;
5693 int loop_phis_first_input_index_ = -1;
5694
5695 // Magle doesn't have projections. Instead, after nodes that return multiple
5696 // values (currently, only maglev::ForInPrepare and maglev::CallBuiltin for
5697 // some builtins), Maglev inserts a GetSecondReturnedValue node, which
5698 // basically just binds kReturnRegister1 to a ValueNode. In the
5699 // Maglev->Turboshaft translation, when we emit a builtin call with multiple
5700 // return values, we set {second_return_value_} to the 2nd projection, and
5701 // then use it when translating GetSecondReturnedValue.
5702 V<Object> second_return_value_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
5703
5704 // {maglev_representations_} contains a map from Turboshaft OpIndex to
5705 // ValueRepresentation of the corresponding Maglev node. This is used when
5706 // translating exception phis: they might need to be re-tagged, and we need to
5707 // know the Maglev ValueRepresentation to distinguish between Float64 and
5708 // HoleyFloat64 (both of which would have Float64 RegisterRepresentation in
5709 // Turboshaft, but they need to be tagged differently).
5710 ZoneAbslFlatHashMap<OpIndex, maglev::ValueRepresentation>
5711 maglev_representations_;
5712
5713 GeneratorAnalyzer generator_analyzer_;
5714 static constexpr int kDefaultSwitchVarValue = -1;
5715 // {is_visiting_generator_main_switch_} is true if the function is a resumable
5716 // generator, and the current input block is the main dispatch switch for
5717 // resuming the generator.
5718 bool is_visiting_generator_main_switch_ = false;
5719 // {on_generator_switch_loop_} is true if the current input block is a loop
5720 // that used to be bypassed by generator resumes, and thus that needs a
5721 // secondary generator dispatch switch.
5722 bool on_generator_switch_loop_ = false;
5723 // {header_switch_input_} is the value on which secondary generator switches
5724 // should switch.
5725 Variable header_switch_input_;
5726 // When secondary dispatch switches for generators are created,
5727 // {loop_default_generator_value_} is used as the default inputs for
5728 // {header_switch_input_} for edges that weren't manually inserted in the
5729 // translation for generators.
5730 V<Word32> loop_default_generator_value_ = V<Word32>::Invalid();
5731 // If the main generator switch bypasses some loop headers, we'll need to
5732 // add an additional predecessor to these loop headers to get rid of the
5733 // bypass. If we do so, we'll need a dummy input for the loop Phis, which
5734 // we create here.
5735 V<Object> dummy_object_input_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
5736 V<Word32> dummy_word32_input_ = V<Word32>::Invalid();
5737 V<Float64> dummy_float64_input_ = V<Float64>::Invalid();
5738 // {maglev_generator_context_node_} is the 1st Maglev node that load the
5739 // context from the generator. Because of the removal of loop header bypasses,
5740 // we can end up using this node in place that's not dominated by the block
5741 // defining this node. To fix this problem, when loading the context from the
5742 // generator for the 1st time, we set {generator_context_}, and in `Map`, we
5743 // always check whether we're trying to get the generator context (=
5744 // {maglev_generator_context_node_}): if so, then we get the value from
5745 // {generator_context_} instead. Note that {generator_context_} is initialized
5746 // with a dummy value (NoContextConstant) so that valid Phis get inserted
5747 // where needed, but by construction, we'll never actually use this dummy
5748 // value.
5749 maglev::NodeBase* maglev_generator_context_node_ = nullptr;
5750 Variable generator_context_;
5751
5752 struct GeneratorSplitEdge {
5753 Block* pre_loop_dst;
5754 Block* inside_loop_target;
5755 int switch_value;
5756 };
5757 std::unordered_map<const maglev::BasicBlock*, std::vector<GeneratorSplitEdge>>
5758 pre_loop_generator_blocks_;
5759
5760 V<NativeContext> native_context_ = V<NativeContext>::Invalid();
5761 V<Object> new_target_param_ = V<Object>::Invalid();
5762 base::SmallVector<int, 16> predecessor_permutation_;
5763
5764 std::optional<BailoutReason>* bailout_;
5765};

5767// A wrapper around GraphBuildingNodeProcessor that takes care of
5768// - skipping nodes when we are in Unreachable code.
5769// - recording source positions.
5770class NodeProcessorBase : public GraphBuildingNodeProcessor {
5771 public:
5772 using GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::GraphBuildingNodeProcessor;
5773
5774 NodeProcessorBase(PipelineData* data, Graph& graph, Zone* temp_zone,
5775 maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* maglev_compilation_unit,
5776 std::optional<BailoutReason>* bailout)
5777 : GraphBuildingNodeProcessor(data, graph, temp_zone,
5778 maglev_compilation_unit, bailout),
5779 graph_(graph),
5780 labeller_(maglev_compilation_unit->graph_labeller()) {}
5781
5782 template <typename NodeT>
5783 maglev::ProcessResult Process(NodeT* node,
5784 const maglev::ProcessingState& state) {
5785 if (GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::Asm().generating_unreachable_operations()) {
5786 // It doesn't matter much whether we return kRemove or kContinue here,
5787 // since we'll be done with the Maglev graph anyway once this phase is
5788 // over. Maglev currently doesn't support kRemove for control nodes, so we
5789 // just return kContinue for simplicity.
5790 return maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue;
5791 }
5792
5793 OpIndex end_index_before = graph_.EndIndex();
5794 maglev::ProcessResult result =
5795 GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::Process(node, state);
5796 DCHECK_IMPLIES(result == maglev::ProcessResult::kContinue &&
5797 !GraphBuildingNodeProcessor::Asm()
5798 .generating_unreachable_operations() &&
5799 maglev::IsValueNode(node->opcode()),
5800 IsMapped(node));
5801
5802 // Recording the SourcePositions of the OpIndex that were just created.
5803 SourcePosition source = labeller_->GetNodeProvenance(node).position;
5804 for (OpIndex idx = end_index_before; idx != graph_.EndIndex();
5805 idx = graph_.NextIndex(idx)) {
5806 graph_.source_positions()[idx] = source;
5807 }
5808
5809 return result;
5810 }
5811
5812 private:
5813 Graph& graph_;
5814 maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller* labeller_;
5815};
5816
5817void PrintBytecode(PipelineData& data,
5818 maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo* compilation_info) {
5819 DCHECK(data.info()->trace_turbo_graph());
5820 maglev::MaglevCompilationUnit* top_level_unit =
5821 compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit();
5822 CodeTracer* code_tracer = data.GetCodeTracer();
5823 CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(code_tracer);
5824 tracing_scope.stream()
5825 << "\n----- Bytecode before MaglevGraphBuilding -----\n"
5826 << std::endl;
5827 tracing_scope.stream() << "Function: "
5828 << Brief(*compilation_info->toplevel_function())
5829 << std::endl;
5830 BytecodeArray::Disassemble(top_level_unit->bytecode().object(),
5831 tracing_scope.stream());
5832 Print(*top_level_unit->feedback().object(), tracing_scope.stream());
5833}
5834
5835void PrintMaglevGraph(PipelineData& data,
5836 maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
5837 maglev::Graph* maglev_graph, const char* msg) {
5838 CodeTracer* code_tracer = data.GetCodeTracer();
5839 CodeTracer::StreamScope tracing_scope(code_tracer);
5840 tracing_scope.stream() << "\n----- " << msg << " -----" << std::endl;
5841 maglev::PrintGraph(tracing_scope.stream(), compilation_info, maglev_graph);
5842}
5843
5844// TODO(dmercadier, nicohartmann): consider doing some of these optimizations on
5845// the Turboshaft graph after the Maglev->Turboshaft translation. For instance,
5846// MaglevPhiRepresentationSelector is the Maglev equivalent of Turbofan's
5847// SimplifiedLowering, but is much less powerful (doesn't take truncations into
5848// account, doesn't do proper range analysis, doesn't run a fixpoint
5849// analysis...).
5850void RunMaglevOptimizations(PipelineData* data,
5851 maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo* compilation_info,
5852 maglev::MaglevGraphBuilder& maglev_graph_builder,
5853 maglev::Graph* maglev_graph) {
5854 // Phi untagging.
5855 {
5856 maglev::GraphProcessor<maglev::MaglevPhiRepresentationSelector> processor(
5857 &maglev_graph_builder);
5858 processor.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
5859 }
5860
5861 if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
5862 PrintMaglevGraph(*data, compilation_info, maglev_graph,
5863 "After phi untagging");
5864 }
5865
5866 // Escape analysis.
5867 {
5868 maglev::GraphMultiProcessor<maglev::AnyUseMarkingProcessor> processor;
5869 processor.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
5870 }
5871
5872#ifdef DEBUG
5873 maglev::GraphProcessor<maglev::MaglevGraphVerifier> verifier(
5874 compilation_info);
5875 verifier.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
5876#endif
5877
5878 // Dead nodes elimination (which, amongst other things, cleans up the left
5879 // overs of escape analysis).
5880 {
5881 maglev::GraphMultiProcessor<maglev::DeadNodeSweepingProcessor> processor(
5882 maglev::DeadNodeSweepingProcessor{compilation_info});
5883 processor.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
5884 }
5885
5886 if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
5887 PrintMaglevGraph(*data, compilation_info, maglev_graph,
5888 "After escape analysis and dead node sweeping");
5889 }
5890}
5891
5892std::optional<BailoutReason> MaglevGraphBuildingPhase::Run(PipelineData* data,
5893 Zone* temp_zone,
5894 Linkage* linkage) {
5895 JSHeapBroker* broker = data->broker();
5896 UnparkedScopeIfNeeded unparked_scope(broker);
5897
5898 std::unique_ptr<maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo> compilation_info =
5899 maglev::MaglevCompilationInfo::NewForTurboshaft(
5900 data->isolate(), broker, data->info()->closure(),
5901 data->info()->osr_offset(),
5902 data->info()->function_context_specializing());
5903
5904 // We need to be certain that the parameter count reported by our output
5905 // Code object matches what the code we compile expects. Otherwise, this
5906 // may lead to effectively signature mismatches during function calls. This
5907 // CHECK is a defense-in-depth measure to ensure this doesn't happen.
5908 SBXCHECK_EQ(compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit()->parameter_count(),
5909 linkage->GetIncomingDescriptor()->ParameterSlotCount());
5910
5911 if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
5912 PrintBytecode(*data, compilation_info.get());
5913 }
5914
5915 LocalIsolate* local_isolate = broker->local_isolate()
5916 ? broker->local_isolate()
5917 : broker->isolate()->AsLocalIsolate();
5918 maglev::Graph* maglev_graph =
5919 maglev::Graph::New(temp_zone, data->info()->is_osr());
5920
5921 // We always create a MaglevGraphLabeller in order to record source positions.
5922 compilation_info->set_graph_labeller(new maglev::MaglevGraphLabeller());
5923
5924 maglev::MaglevGraphBuilder maglev_graph_builder(
5925 local_isolate, compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit(),
5926 maglev_graph);
5927 maglev_graph_builder.Build();
5928
5929 if (V8_UNLIKELY(data->info()->trace_turbo_graph())) {
5930 PrintMaglevGraph(*data, compilation_info.get(), maglev_graph,
5931 "After graph building");
5932 }
5933
5934 RunMaglevOptimizations(data, compilation_info.get(), maglev_graph_builder,
5935 maglev_graph);
5936
5937 // TODO(nicohartmann): Should we have source positions here?
5938 data->InitializeGraphComponent(nullptr);
5939
5940 std::optional<BailoutReason> bailout;
5941 maglev::GraphProcessor<NodeProcessorBase, true> builder(
5942 data, data->graph(), temp_zone,
5943 compilation_info->toplevel_compilation_unit(), &bailout);
5944 builder.ProcessGraph(maglev_graph);
5945
5946 // Copying {inlined_functions} from Maglev to Turboshaft.
5947 for (OptimizedCompilationInfo::InlinedFunctionHolder holder :
5948 maglev_graph->inlined_functions()) {
5949 data->info()->inlined_functions().push_back(holder);
5950 }
5951
5952 if (V8_UNLIKELY(bailout.has_value() &&
5953 (v8_flags.trace_turbo || v8_flags.trace_turbo_graph))) {
5954 // If we've bailed out, then we've probably left the graph in some kind of
5955 // invalid state. We Reset it now, so that --trace-turbo doesn't try to
5956 // print an invalid graph.
5957 data->graph().Reset();
5958 }
5959
5960 return bailout;
5961}
